Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.24,0:17:08.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,要我打给孩子他妈吗\N{\rENG}Should I call his mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.82,0:17:11.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要 别再打了\N{\rENG}No, please. Never again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.43,0:17:13.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,他甚至还不懂怎么扔棒球\N{\rENG}I mean the kid doesn't even know how to throw a baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:15.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁在乎啊\N{\rENG}Who cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.98,0:17:20.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,他用肘发力 扔得跟小女生一样\N{\rENG}He just, he eads with his elbow, he throws like a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.05,0:17:20.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不能怪你\N{\rENG}It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.84,0:17:22.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 就都怪我\N{\rENG}No, it is my fault,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.95,0:17:25.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,父亲就该教会儿子这些\N{\rENG}a father is supposed to teach you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.04,0:17:26.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,他只是不喜欢打棒球 不能怪他\N{\rENG}Ok. he just doesn't like baseball, you can't blame him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.71,0:17:29.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是用这个例子来比喻做其他事情\N{\rENG}It's just an example, it's a metaphor for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:32.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,他马上就十四岁了 他需要父亲的陪伴\N{\rENG}He's turning 14 and he needs to be with his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:38.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰西 我是不会搬去芝加哥的\N{\rENG}Jesse, I'm not moving to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.40,0:17:40.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么 我有说吗\N{\rENG}What? Did I ask you to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.74,0:17:41.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怎么会这样想\N{\rENG}Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.65,0:17:42.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是想到什么说什么\N{\rENG}I'm just thinking out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:45.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾经答应过自己不要这么冲动\N{\rENG}I mean, this is the one thing I promised myself I would never do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.96,0:17:48.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我看开了 冲动就冲动吧\N{\rENG}And I look up and I'm doing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.54,0:17:50.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着 你是个好父亲\N{\rENG}Listen, you're a wonderful father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:52.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,他珍惜这段父子关系\N{\rENG}He loves the relationship you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.33,0:17:53.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,他珍惜你给他写的信\N{\rENG}he loves the letters you send him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.59,0:17:55.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的信他连看都没看\N{\rENG}He doesn't even read the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:55.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,他当然看了你的信\N{\rENG}Of course he reads them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.79,0:17:56.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,他只是没有给你回…\N{\rENG}he just doesn't complement the writing the way you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.70,0:17:59.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是知道 要是错过了这几年\N{\rENG}I just know that if I miss these years,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.03,0:18:00.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,就永远也补不回来了\N{\rENG}they are never coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.23,0:18:04.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,老天\N{\rENG}Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.99,0:18:05.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.74,0:18:08.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是结束的时刻\N{\rENG}This is where it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:11.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在说什么\N{\rENG}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:13.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这就是人们分手的节奏  - 老天\N{\rENG}- This is how people start breaking up.  - Oh my god.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:16.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是的  - 你这是小题大做\N{\rENG}- No, no, no.  - You just jumped off a cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.10,0:18:17.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 我要记下今天\N{\rENG}No, no. I'm marking this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.12,0:18:19.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在今天 你引爆了\N{\rENG}this is the day you light the ticking bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.52,0:18:23.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,了结我们性命的定时炸弹\N{\rENG}that will destroy our lives, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:24.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的 首先\N{\rENG}Ok, well, first off,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:26.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是引爆定时炸弹\N{\rENG}you don't light a ticking bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:27.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,而是安装 它有定时器\N{\rENG}you set it, it has a timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.72,0:18:29.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 所以才能定时  - 是吗 管他呢\N{\rENG}- That's why it ticks.  - Oh, yeah. whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.11,0:18:31.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在已经开始倒计时了\N{\rENG}You know what? It's ticking right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.81,0:18:33.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,说什么也没用\N{\rENG}And this is how it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.83,0:18:34.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你自己不高兴\N{\rENG}You are unhappy and blame it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.89,0:18:36.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,却怪别人满怀怨恨\N{\rENG}on the other person Resentment grows,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.09,0:18:37.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,等一切都崩溃了 你就提出分手\N{\rENG}everything falls apart and you break up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.60,0:18:39.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你就是这样  - 你这样做只是想让我闭嘴\N{\rENG}- That's it.  - You are just doing this to shut me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.39,0:18:40.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 根本不是\N{\rENG}Not at all! Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:41.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是 而且你也这样做了\N{\rENG}No, you are, and that's what you are doing, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:43.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 我是觉得很惊讶\N{\rENG}No, I'm actually surprised,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.09,0:18:43.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,在经历了那么多…\N{\rENG}we've lasted this long...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:45.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的 直接说你想说的\N{\rENG}Ok. So here it comes out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.26,0:18:47.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们本形同陌路 但却萍水相逢\N{\rENG}We are on parallel tracks a while but now the tracks have crossed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:49.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在却要分道扬镳了\N{\rENG}and I'm going west and you're going east.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.70,0:18:51.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是这样分手的\N{\rENG}And believe me this is how it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.48,0:18:53.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,我早就知道了 就像卡特琳跟亚历山大…\N{\rENG}I've seen it, ok? Katrin, Alexandre...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.77,0:18:55.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你在开玩笑吧  - 没有\N{\rENG}- You're kidding, right?  - Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:18:58.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,你可以当玩笑 但我是认真的\N{\rENG}I'm kidding, and I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.03,0:19:00.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.17,0:19:02.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,别那么…\N{\rENG}Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:05.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 就这样了  - 我想看古代遗迹\N{\rENG}- This is it.  - I want watch ancient ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.02,0:19:08.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,那里关门了\N{\rENG}Oh, they were closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.95,0:19:11.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,宝贝 下次去机场的时候\N{\rENG}Sweetie you know what, we decided to catch them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.69,0:19:13.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们再去看 好吗\N{\rENG}when we're on the way back to the airport. Ok?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:15.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 我们会早点启程 对吧\N{\rENG}Exactly, we'll leave early, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.85,0:19:17.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的苹果呢\N{\rENG}What happened to my apple?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.21,0:19:22.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的苹果…\N{\rENG}Your apple...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.63,0:19:25.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的苹果吗 已经被你吃完了啊\N{\rENG}Ta pomme, mais elle était finie cette pomme.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:28.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吧\N{\rENG}Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:42.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们去买冰淇淋吧 我们大概一点出发\N{\rENG}Allez vous chercher des glaces, on y passe à une heure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.71,0:19:46.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 把清单拿来  - 我没拿\N{\rENG}- Give me the list.  - I don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.77,0:19:49.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你钱包里 钱包拿来\N{\rENG}It's in your wallet! And your wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.40,0:19:54.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是将军\N{\rENG}Ok, I am the General.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.56,0:19:58.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,妮娜上尉 去帮我找厕纸\N{\rENG}Capitaine Nina, vous allez me chercher du papier toillette.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:19:59.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,遵命\N{\rENG}Oui!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:00.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁任命你当将军的\N{\rENG}Who made you General?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:02.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是将军 好吗\N{\rENG}The General, ok?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.47,0:20:04.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,艾拉上尉 您去找卷纸\N{\rENG}Capitaine Ella, vous allez chercher les roules papiers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.36,0:20:06.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在商店最里面的右边\N{\rENG}qui sont tout au fond du magasin à droite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.32,0:20:07.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 遵命  - 待命\N{\rENG}- Oui!  - à vos ordres!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.56,0:20:09.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,特别警告 你什么都不许拿\N{\rENG}Private Clean-up, you don't touch anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:12.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的 长官\N{\rENG}D'accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:17.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,别走太快\N{\rENG}Il vous faut pas aller trop vite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.90,0:20:28.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,妮娜 放到厨房去\N{\rENG}Nina, la cuisine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.91,0:20:34.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,妮娜 听到没\N{\rENG}Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.53,0:20:55.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的队友呢 我的队友呢\N{\rENG}Where is my team! Where is my team!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:12.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,去帮我找点番茄过来\N{\rENG}Allez me chercher des tomates.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.29,0:21:13.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,那边 那边\N{\rENG}Là-bas, là-bas!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:24.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是这个吗  - 是的\N{\rENG}- Celles-là?  - Ah... oui!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.42,0:21:29.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,挑红的\N{\rENG}The red one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.19,0:21:34.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这个行吗  - 很好\N{\rENG}- Celle-là?  - Très bien!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.21,0:21:38.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,辣椒 接住\N{\rENG}Ok! Pepper!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:42.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实两本我都读过\N{\rENG}Actually I read them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.83,0:21:44.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,第一本叫《彼时此刻》\N{\rENG}The first one is called "That time",
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.10,0:21:45.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,第二本叫《此时此刻》\N{\rENG}and the second one is "This time".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:46.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,不对 第一本叫《此时此刻》\N{\rENG}No, the first is "This time",
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:47.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,第二本叫《彼时此刻》\N{\rENG}and the second is "That time".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.31,0:21:47.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.93,0:21:50.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们还开玩笑 第一本帮我们组建家庭\N{\rENG}We've got a joke in our family that "This" Brought us together,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.78,0:21:52.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,第二本帮我们还房贷\N{\rENG}and "That" Paid for our apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.25,0:21:53.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.31,0:21:55.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,但瑟琳的角色有点怪 伙计\N{\rENG}But it must be a little weird for Celine, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.19,0:21:57.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,她在书中的表现 不觉得吗\N{\rENG}The way that she's in the book. No?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:21:59.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,会吗 可能她已习以为常了\N{\rENG}Why? I think she has gotten used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.15,0:22:01.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,第二本写得真香艳 伙计\N{\rENG}But the second one is sexy, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.66,0:22:03.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,男主角错过飞机后 他们就把窗户关上\N{\rENG}When he misses the plane and they blackout the windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:05.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后没日没夜地做爱\N{\rENG}and have sex for days and days and days.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.40,0:22:06.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像明天就是世界末日一样\N{\rENG}Like there's no tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.61,0:22:10.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们真是那样吗\N{\rENG}Did you guys actually do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:12.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,是真的 对吧\N{\rENG}You did that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.21,0:22:14.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看过杰西的第三本书没\N{\rENG}Have you read Jesse's third book?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.20,0:22:16.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,事实上比前两本写得好\N{\rENG}It's actually better than the first two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:17.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,反正写的时间\N{\rENG}It certainly took longer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.09,0:22:18.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,比前两本加起来都要长\N{\rENG}to write than the first two put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.96,0:22:21.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没看第三本 我老婆给我了\N{\rENG}No, the third one I didn't read, I mean my wife gave it to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.37,0:22:23.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我觉得有点长\N{\rENG}but it's a just a little bit too long for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.21,0:22:25.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,连书名也很长 叫什么来着\N{\rENG}Even the title is long. What's the title?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.07,0:22:27.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,《长年上演的小众话剧\N{\rENG}"Temporary cast members of a long-running
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.38,0:22:30.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,中的临时演员们》\N{\rENG}{\fe238}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b1}{\c&HFFFFFF&}{\3c&H2F2F2F&}{\4c&H000000&}but little-seen production of a play called fleeting"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.39,0:22:32.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我说得没错吧\N{\rENG}Well, exactly my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.76,0:22:34.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,不止是你 其他人也觉得它太长了\N{\rENG}You're not alone, everybody else thought it was too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.95,0:22:38.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这本书写得更好 更有野心\N{\rENG}It is a better book, it's so much more ambitious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:43.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说什么\N{\rENG}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.60,0:22:46.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说 三本书他都喜欢\N{\rENG}No, he says, he likes... he likes all the books.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.41,0:22:48.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\rENG}He does.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.43,0:22:53.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这里 这里棒极了\N{\rENG}I mean I love it here. This place is amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.65,0:22:55.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,番茄也棒极了\N{\rENG}those tomatoes are so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.93,0:23:00.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,闻起来都觉得好吃 真好闻\N{\rENG}I can smell them, they smell so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.57,0:23:02.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 帕特里克对此引以为豪\N{\rENG}Yeah. Patrick is very proud of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.70,0:23:05.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道这样想很蠢 不过…\N{\rENG}I know it's stupid but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.37,0:23:06.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,当决定离开巴黎到这来时\N{\rENG}When we were about to leave Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.96,0:23:08.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实我很担心\N{\rENG}I was all nervous we were about to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.31,0:23:10.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在要走了 却又舍不得\N{\rENG}And now we're about to leave and I do not wanna go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.52,0:23:13.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 为什么会担心  - 是啊 为什么\N{\rENG}- Why were you nervous?  - Yes, why was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.68,0:23:15.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道 这地方承载着\N{\rENG}I do not know. this place is so full of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.76,0:23:17.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,千百年的悲欢离合\N{\rENG}thousands of years of myth and tragedies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.82,0:23:19.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我害怕有不好的事要发生\N{\rENG}and I thought something tragic was gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.42,0:23:22.51,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}弥诺陶洛斯{\u0}：古希腊神话中人身牛头怪物\N{\rCHS}你怕弥诺陶洛斯会来吃你的小孩\N{\rENG}You thought the Minotaur was going to eat your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.51,0:23:23.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.24,0:23:25.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rENG}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.21,0:23:31.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些天来 我有了一个想法\N{\rENG}All the time I've been here I've been working on this idea about
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.25,0:23:34.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,是关于一群大脑异常的人\N{\rENG}a group of different people with all these brain abnormalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.56,0:23:37.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想从他们的独特视角出发\N{\rENG}So the book would be like a day in their life,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:39.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,来观察他们日常生活中的一天\N{\rENG}from all their unique points of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.70,0:23:42.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,就比如有位老太太\N{\rENG}Right? Like there's this older lady who has the condition that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.28,0:23:44.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,她会沉浸在似曾相识的感觉当中\N{\rENG}makes you feel like you're in a perpetual state of deja vu.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.85,0:23:46.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,每一个经历过的场景\N{\rENG}And every single experience she has,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.60,0:23:48.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,她都会觉得似曾相识\N{\rENG}she feels like she's had it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.02,0:23:49.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,她有可能坐在这\N{\rENG}I mean she could be sitting here with us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.44,0:23:51.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,很正常地跟我们聊天\N{\rENG}talking seemingly functional right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.45,0:23:53.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实她脑子里在想\N{\rENG}And in her head she's thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.93,0:23:55.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,这话他刚刚不是说过了吗\N{\rENG}didn't he already say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.07,0:23:56.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,会不会我们昨天也在这\N{\rENG}I mean, weren't we here yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.26,0:23:58.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,展开了一模一样的谈话\N{\rENG}Having this exact same conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:23:59.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像有即视感\N{\rENG}So just like deja vu?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.27,0:24:00.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 不过更频繁\N{\rENG}Yeah, except all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.48,0:24:03.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,她所接触过的每一样事物\N{\rENG}That's the thing, right, everything she takes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.30,0:24:06.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,一份早餐 一张报纸 一场电影\N{\rENG}A breakfast, a newspaper, a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.19,0:24:08.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,她都认为自己早就经历过\N{\rENG}She is convinced she's encountered it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.20,0:24:09.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种情况真的存在吗\N{\rENG}Is that a real condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.22,0:24:12.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 叫做持续性即视…\N{\rENG}Yeah, it is called persistent Dejav...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.74,0:24:14.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,确实存在 我不会拼而已\N{\rENG}It's real but I can't pronounce it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.72,0:24:19.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,接着是截然相反的两个人\N{\rENG}There are two other characters with facial recognition extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.07,0:24:22.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个二十年来从来都认不出自己的老婆\N{\rENG}There is one guy and he can not recognize his wife for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.10,0:24:25.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,他看着镜子中的自己\N{\rENG}He looks at himself in the mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.45,0:24:29.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,会感到陌生\N{\rENG}and he feels disconnected with that man he's looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.22,0:24:31.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,另一个角色则刚好相反\N{\rENG}And the other character is the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.60,0:24:34.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,这位中年主妇有着\N{\rENG}A middle-aged housewife with a categorical exacting memory
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.92,0:24:36.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,对人过目不忘的本领\N{\rENG}of every face she has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.28,0:24:39.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽在大城市 对她而言却与小城镇无异\N{\rENG}And she lives in a big city but to her it is a small town.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.03,0:24:40.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,就比如有辆计程车经过 她就会想\N{\rENG}Like a taxi drives past and she thinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.74,0:24:44.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,那不就是三年前的圣诞节\N{\rENG}"Oh that's the driver who dropped me off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:46.05,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}孚日广场{\u0}：巴黎最古老的广场\N{\rCHS}在孚日广场放下我的司机吗\N{\rENG}at Place des Vosges three Christmases ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.05,0:24:48.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,就比如看见有位老太太走在街上\N{\rENG}Like some old lady, walking on the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.09,0:24:51.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,她就会想 她是去年在地铁上\N{\rENG}she thinks, "Oh! She sat two seats down from me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.06,0:24:52.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,坐在我后两位的老太太\N{\rENG}on the metro last year."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.26,0:24:54.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以她对遇见的每个人\N{\rENG}So everyone she meets, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.40,0:24:56.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,都感到亲密无间\N{\rENG}to her feels intimate and connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.43,0:24:57.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你说的第一个\N{\rENG}Well, I'm like the first guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.87,0:25:00.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为大多时候我也是见人就忘\N{\rENG}I feel connected to nothing most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.94,0:25:03.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿奇里斯 安娜 你们好\N{\rENG}Hey! Achilleas! Anna! Hey guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.24,0:25:09.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,看这孩子 他暑假过得比我们都要好\N{\rENG}Look at this kid, he is having the best summer of us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.31,0:25:20.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以你要说的就是这三个角色 对吗\N{\rENG}So, you were saying these three characters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.57,0:25:22.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 这只是那一群人当中的三个角色\N{\rENG}No. It's not just three characters, it's a whole group of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.67,0:25:24.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我现在也有一章是写\N{\rENG}Like I'm working on a Chapter right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.70,0:25:26.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个叫阿奇里斯的年轻希腊男子\N{\rENG}about a young Greek man named Achilleas.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.96,0:25:28.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我吗  - 是以你命名的\N{\rENG}- Me?  - Well, he's named after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.49,0:25:30.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个人陷入了迷阵\N{\rENG}And this guy is caught in a loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.79,0:25:33.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他看来一切都是转瞬即逝的\N{\rENG}all he sees is the transient nature of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.34,0:25:35.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像他看到这片海\N{\rENG}Like he looks out to the sea, and he thinks of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.54,0:25:37.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,他想到的是它干涸和堆满化石的一天\N{\rENG}it's gonna be dry and littered with fossils.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.66,0:25:41.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么说呢 听上去有点做作\N{\rENG}Well, I do not know. Sounds a little pretentious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.58,0:25:43.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 不会做作 我保证\N{\rENG}No no no, it won't be pretentious, I promise, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.27,0:25:45.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,会很有趣 真的很有趣\N{\rENG}It's gonna be funny. Really funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.02,0:25:48.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,他捡到一本书马上想到的是\N{\rENG}He picks up a book and immediately wonders,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.10,0:25:50.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,最后读到这本书的人会是谁\N{\rENG}who's gonna be the last person to read this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.24,0:25:53.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这有趣吗  - 有时候我也会那样想\N{\rENG}- And that's funny?  - Sometimes I kind of think like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.11,0:25:56.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以他不喜欢乳房啊 车啊 饮酒啊\N{\rENG}Ok, so he does not get excited about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.01,0:25:57.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,对这些都不感兴趣\N{\rENG}tits, cars, booze, nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.60,0:26:00.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 一心只想着死亡  - 也不全是死亡\N{\rENG}- Just thinks about death.  - Well, not so much death.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.10,0:26:02.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,像变了一个人似的\N{\rENG}It's like transformation, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.75,0:26:05.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于未来过于杞人忧天\N{\rENG}like he is seeing too far in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.01,0:26:07.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好吧  - 我喜欢这个想法\N{\rENG}- Ok.  - I like this idea for a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.77,0:26:10.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过你应该加个像我一样的老头上去\N{\rENG}But you should add a character of an old man like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.57,0:26:13.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个连早餐吃过什么都会忘的人\N{\rENG}A poor sapp who can't remember what he ate for breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.07,0:26:15.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,但对于十四岁那年在珠儿酒吧\N{\rENG}But still hear the song that was playing,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.25,0:26:17.26,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}希拉·坎贝尔{\u0}：八十年代美国女影星\N{\rCHS}看到希拉·坎贝尔半裸跳舞时\N{\rENG}when Sheila Campbell danced topless
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.26,0:26:19.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,所听到的音乐记忆犹新\N{\rENG}on the bar at Jurees when he was 14 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.13,0:26:20.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,这提议很不错\N{\rENG}That would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.80,0:26:24.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些人都在时间里迷失了 对吧\N{\rENG}Ok. you have these people lost in time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.72,0:26:26.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们之间的联系在哪 是通过做爱吗\N{\rENG}What is the connection? Are they gonna have sex?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.78,0:26:27.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,难道不需要把他们联系到一起吗\N{\rENG}Don't you need something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.80,0:26:30.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们并非迷失在时间里 而是感知出了问题\N{\rENG}It's not time they have lost in, right? It's like, perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.69,0:26:31.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样说吧\N{\rENG}That's the deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.26,0:26:35.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我打算把整部小说设置在一部电影当中\N{\rENG}I'm thinking of setting the whole novel at a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.03,0:26:36.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,每个角色都会跟\N{\rENG}Like every character in some way
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.60,0:26:38.93,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}《码头风云》{\u0}：马龙白兰度主演的奥斯卡获奖影片\N{\rCHS}《码头风云》这部电影产生一定的联系\N{\rENG}comes into contact with the film "On the Waterfront".
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.24,0:26:40.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,看过《码头风云》没\N{\rENG}Have you seen On the Waterfront?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.54,0:26:41.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,《码头风云》吗\N{\rENG}On the Waterfront?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:43.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,白兰度演的吗\N{\rENG}With Brando?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.55,0:26:46.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,书的第一章发生于一九五四年的一个周末\N{\rENG}The first chapter of the book is opening at a weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.88,0:26:48.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,在时代广场\N{\rENG}in Times Square in 1954.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.62,0:26:50.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,有着持续性即视感的老太太\N{\rENG}That old lady with perpetual deja vu
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.94,0:26:52.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,走去看日场放映\N{\rENG}walks into the matinee screening,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.90,0:26:55.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,但她却满脑子疑惑\N{\rENG}except the whole time she's thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.28,0:26:58.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不是已经看过了吗\N{\rENG}"Haven't I already seen this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.25,0:27:00.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,另外一章发生在一九七九年\N{\rENG}Yeah, and then in another chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.06,0:27:03.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,巴黎的一个电影学习班里\N{\rENG}is a 1979 Paris film studies class.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.24,0:27:05.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,接下来会发生在一九九三年\N{\rENG}Then we have a Kazan
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.02,0:27:08.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,慕尼黑的一场喀山回顾展里\N{\rENG}retrospective in Munich in 1993.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.29,0:27:10.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,这讲的就是时间 怎么不是时间呢\N{\rENG}Well man, that is time. How is that not time?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.83,0:27:14.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,确实与时间有关 但讲的更多的是感知\N{\rENG}Yeah, it's time, but it's more perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.46,0:27:17.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你不喜欢吗  - 我怕你又写很长\N{\rENG}- You don't like it?  - I think it's gonna be too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.38,0:27:22.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢 别听他的 做单车的懂什么\N{\rENG}Well. I like it. Do not listen to him, he makes bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.68,0:27:24.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,记得寄一份到我加勒的地址\N{\rENG}Send it to me in Galles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.88,0:27:25.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是肯定的\N{\rENG}Will do!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.31,0:27:38.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,在法国番茄跟辣椒\N{\rENG}In France we stuff the tomatoes with tomatoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.32,0:27:39.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,会酿上不同的馅\N{\rENG}and the peppers with peppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.53,0:27:42.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,真的吗 我们这都酿同一种馅\N{\rENG}Oh, really? Because we use the same stuffing for both.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.45,0:27:45.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样你就能尝到馅糅合香草的味道\N{\rENG}Because of the way it reacts with the leaves you can taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.53,0:27:46.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.96,0:27:51.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,瑟琳 别酿太满\N{\rENG}Oh, and Celine, make sure you don't stuff them too much,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.68,0:27:54.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,不然待会馅溢出烤炉\N{\rENG}because of the way it overflows in the oven later.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.84,0:27:55.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,会比较难清洁\N{\rENG}It gets kind of nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.79,0:27:57.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,你做的很好 瑟琳\N{\rENG}You're doing fine, Celine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.67,0:28:00.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,千万要记住 别听斯特凡诺斯的\N{\rENG}And especially do not listen to Stefanos here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.15,0:28:03.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没做过这道菜\N{\rENG}Because he has never made this dish before,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.11,0:28:04.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,实际上他就没做过菜\N{\rENG}or any other dish, for that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.24,0:28:18.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,别拿着刀吵架\N{\rENG}Stop fighting with knives!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.24,0:28:21.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,别这样 别拿着刀吵架\N{\rENG}Stop it! Stop fighting with knives!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.55,0:28:23.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们没有吵架 我们是在商量\N{\rENG}We're not fighting, we are negotiating.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.32,0:28:27.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,商量 你们管这叫商量\N{\rENG}Negotiating. That's how you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.16,0:28:29.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇 带着刀的商量啊\N{\rENG}Wow, négociation avec des couteaux!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.78,0:28:32.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,完全正确\N{\rENG}Exactement!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.45,0:28:34.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是我们相处的方式\N{\rENG}It is a system that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.50,0:28:36.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,看来你们找到了适合你们的方式\N{\rENG}So you found the system that works for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.01,0:28:38.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想这就叫磨合\N{\rENG}I thought it was called having a "Relationship".
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.19,0:28:39.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过我喜欢你们的说法 很棒\N{\rENG}But I like system, that's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.85,0:28:41.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这可以了吧  - 可以了\N{\rENG}- That's ready, right?  - That's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.18,0:28:43.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,你呢 你的相处方式是什么\N{\rENG}Toi, c'est quoi ton system?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.06,0:28:48.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是这个  - 不错嘛\N{\rENG}- Celui-là.  - Pas mal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.55,0:28:50.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们以前也那样\N{\rENG}We used to have that system.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.12,0:29:06.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,别游太远\N{\rENG}Not too far you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.59,0:29:47.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想借这顿饭机会\N{\rENG}Alright, I just don't want to let this meal go by
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.41,0:29:49.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,跟在座各位说声谢谢\N{\rENG}without just saying thank you to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.67,0:29:51.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,特别是你 帕特里克\N{\rENG}And especially you, Patrick.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.72,0:29:55.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,这六周多亏有你的招待\N{\rENG}we had no idea what we were getting into these last six weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.14,0:29:56.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在大学里收到一份邀约\N{\rENG}A letter arrives from the university
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.91,0:29:59.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,一位伟大的作家邀请我们\N{\rENG}inviting us to the Southern Peloponnese of Greece
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.92,0:30:02.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,到他希腊南伯罗奔尼萨的旅舍去度假\N{\rENG}to the guesthouse of a great writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.66,0:30:04.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,好啊 为什么拒绝\N{\rENG}Sure! Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.68,0:30:08.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天早上在机场\N{\rENG}And then at the airport earlier today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.82,0:30:10.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克对我说\N{\rENG}Hank turns to me and he says that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.70,0:30:12.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是他度过最棒的暑假\N{\rENG}this has been the greatest summer of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.17,0:30:16.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也一样 谢谢你 帕特里克\N{\rENG}And I have to say the same, so thank you, Patrick!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.42,0:30:18.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不仅要敬你为我和我的家人所做的一切\N{\rENG}And not just for what you done for me and my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.77,0:30:20.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,还要敬你一直以来的慷慨奉献\N{\rENG}But for all the ways that you have given back, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.91,0:30:21.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,敬帕特里克\N{\rENG}To Patrick!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.39,0:30:28.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢 谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you, thank you, thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.86,0:30:30.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我第一次在机场看见你\N{\rENG}you know when I first saw you at the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.88,0:30:33.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我心想 这男的穿成这样\N{\rENG}I thought, no way, a man dressed like that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.57,0:30:35.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么可能是个作家\N{\rENG}could be a man of letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.44,0:30:42.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,但现在我总算找出原因了\N{\rENG}But now. I think I've learned your secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.03,0:30:45.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,在过去十年里也出现过许多优秀的作家\N{\rENG}we've had many great writers over the past decade,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.52,0:30:48.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,但没有一位的妻子比作家本身还要有意思\N{\rENG}but never one who had a partner more interesting than themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.73,0:30:53.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁说不是呢\N{\rENG}I'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.38,0:30:57.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,瑟琳 感谢你和你的女儿\N{\rENG}And Celine, it's been so great to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.34,0:31:00.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,为这里带来了无限的生机\N{\rENG}have you and your daughters' wonderful vitality around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.95,0:31:03.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,同时也很高兴能为你引见\N{\rENG}And I'm so happy you were able to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.13,0:31:05.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的好朋友娜塔莉\N{\rENG}my dear friend Natalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.40,0:31:08.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的丈夫伊莱亚斯跟我情同手足\N{\rENG}Whose husband Elias was like a brother to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.87,0:31:10.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,对上校的事我感到很抱歉\N{\rENG}I'm so sorry about the Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.31,0:31:12.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我说的是上次…  - 是我的错\N{\rENG}- I mean the early...  - I should... It was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.43,0:31:16.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我跟安娜也要感谢这次暑假邀约\N{\rENG}Thanks for including Anna and me this summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.91,0:31:18.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为他平常只会让我去工作\N{\rENG}Because you know he usually puts me to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.70,0:31:19.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我把安娜带来时\N{\rENG}But when I bring Anna,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.80,0:31:21.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,他让我坐在大人桌上\N{\rENG}he let me sit at the table of the grown-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.45,0:31:24.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到大人桌\N{\rENG}Welcome to the grown-up's table!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.17,0:31:29.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们俩在一起多久了\N{\rENG}How long have you two been together?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.05,0:31:31.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,从上个暑假到现在\N{\rENG}Since last summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.07,0:31:32.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们一年前在这里邂逅\N{\rENG}We met one year ago here,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.37,0:31:34.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是在我要回雅典之前\N{\rENG}in my last days with Grandpa,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.38,0:31:35.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,陪伴爷爷的最后几天\N{\rENG}before I had to go back to Athens.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.70,0:31:37.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 我们在闭幕晚会上相遇\N{\rENG}Yes, we met at my closing night cast party.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.75,0:31:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时候我在剧院演莎翁的戏\N{\rENG}I was doing Shakespeare in the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.71,0:31:41.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你演什么角色\N{\rENG}Who did you play?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.98,0:31:44.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我演《冬天的故事》里的潘狄塔\N{\rENG}I was Perdita. The winter's tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.00,0:31:45.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,她演得很好\N{\rENG}She was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.65,0:31:47.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,帕特里克 记得我们看的那次吗\N{\rENG}Remember, Patrick, we went to there?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.47,0:31:50.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,潘狄塔 当你跳舞时\N{\rENG}Perdita, "When you do dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.03,0:31:51.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我希望你是浩淼海洋中的一道波浪\N{\rENG}I wish you a wave o' th' sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.74,0:31:53.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样就已足够\N{\rENG}that you might ever do Nothing but that."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.24,0:31:56.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,你演得\N{\rENG}The way you just performed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.78,0:31:59.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,比剧中那小伙子好多了\N{\rENG}that was much better than the guy in the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.52,0:32:01.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们至今还对那部剧津津乐道\N{\rENG}People are still talking about that production.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.71,0:32:04.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,但更棒的在宴会后 那是我俩头次见面\N{\rENG}But the after-party was even better, it was when we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.68,0:32:08.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,对 我开着老款的BSA型摩托车\N{\rENG}Yeah, I had an old BSA motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.55,0:32:09.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,不错\N{\rENG}Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.33,0:32:11.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,整晚我们都在兜风\N{\rENG}So... we drove around all night,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.47,0:32:14.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,最后我们开回剧院\N{\rENG}and then I had to drive her back to the theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.13,0:32:15.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,去拿她的东西\N{\rENG}to get her stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.22,0:32:16.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时天已经蒙蒙亮了\N{\rENG}And it was the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.56,0:32:17.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我永远忘不了那一刻\N{\rENG}And I'll never forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.61,0:32:20.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是个露天剧场 可容纳一万两千人\N{\rENG}It was outdoors and it seats 12000 people,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.38,0:32:22.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,空空荡荡的\N{\rENG}and it was now completely empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.75,0:32:25.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,她径直走到最后一排坐下\N{\rENG}And she was sitting way up in the back row.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.60,0:32:28.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以 我登上舞台\N{\rENG}So... I went up on stage
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.22,0:32:30.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,低声对她说\N{\rENG}and whispered to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.79,0:32:32.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,声音的传播好奇妙\N{\rENG}The acoustics there are incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.67,0:32:35.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我先看到他的嘴在动\N{\rENG}I could see his mouth move and then 3 seconds later,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.82,0:32:37.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,三秒后我才听到他的声音\N{\rENG}I could hear his voice in my ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.92,0:32:39.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说的什么\N{\rENG}What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.11,0:32:43.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 好  - 好\N{\rENG}- OK!  - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.02,0:32:43.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,小秘密\N{\rENG}It is private.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.94,0:32:47.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她飞回巴黎住些日子\N{\rENG}And then she had to fly back to Paris a couple of days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.83,0:32:48.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们怎么联络呢\N{\rENG}How did you keep in touch?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.96,0:32:49.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们用视频聊天\N{\rENG}We Skyped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.97,0:32:51.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,几乎天天聊\N{\rENG}Pretty much every day since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.56,0:32:53.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们睡觉时\N{\rENG}And we are in bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.19,0:32:55.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,必然会把电脑放在枕边\N{\rENG}we have a thing of putting our laptop by the pillow,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.90,0:32:57.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,看着对方一起入睡\N{\rENG}and... falling asleep together
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.69,0:32:59.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着又新鲜又浪漫\N{\rENG}Oh that's the new romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.92,0:33:02.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,等醒来 屏幕基本都定格在\N{\rENG}And when I wake up the screen is usually frozen
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.97,0:33:06.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,一些很滑稽的姿势 就像这样\N{\rENG}and Anna's face is in some funny position like...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:10.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我来问个问题\N{\rENG}Can I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.74,0:33:13.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们视频聊天时\N{\rENG}When you guys Skype
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.84,0:33:16.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,有点小疯狂的事情没有\N{\rENG}Do you, you know... do you go a little crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.39,0:33:18.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,天 你的节操呢\N{\rENG}My God! You're being so vulgar!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.02,0:33:19.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,这无关什么节操\N{\rENG}No, nothing to vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.06,0:33:20.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是个对虚拟世界比较感性趣的\N{\rENG}I'm just being a amateur anthropologist
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.92,0:33:24.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,只停留在理论水平的业余人类学家\N{\rENG}who is interested in the virtual world on a theoretical level.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.10,0:33:25.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,你倒成了人类学家了\N{\rENG}Now you're an anthropologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.60,0:33:28.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 题目是未来的性爱\N{\rENG}Yes, the sex of the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.36,0:33:30.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我这不是胡扯\N{\rENG}And I'm not making this up but it's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.79,0:33:34.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,将来会在你的生殖器里放入个装置\N{\rENG}gonna be just like plugging in something in your genitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.35,0:33:37.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,冒犯了 可以根据你的需要\N{\rENG}I'm sorry. And you can have sexual intercourse
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.20,0:33:38.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,来选择跟谁性交\N{\rENG}with anyone of your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.90,0:33:42.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,专门为你定制\N{\rENG}You'll be able to programme in all your preferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.06,0:33:44.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,满足你的要求\N{\rENG}You'll be able to type in exactly what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.65,0:33:46.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,比如让玛丽莲·梦露 在你耳边轻语\N{\rENG}Marilyn Monroe to whisper in your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.99,0:33:49.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,听起来超赞 没错\N{\rENG}I might like that! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.78,0:33:54.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么不呢\N{\rENG}I mean... Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.06,0:33:55.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,越来越多的人们\N{\rENG}More and more of our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.49,0:33:58.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,把时间放到了虚拟世界上\N{\rENG}experiences are taking place in the virtual world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.16,0:33:59.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.75,0:34:02.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是作家 如果有一天电脑能写出\N{\rENG}And you're a writer. How are you gonna feel when
