Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.35,0:41:33.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就想 天长地久相爱\N{\rENG}I wonder if this idea of a love
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.45,0:41:36.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种事还和我们有关吗\N{\rENG}affair that lasts forever is still relevant to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.65,0:41:38.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,都知道\N{\rENG}I mean we know that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.23,0:41:40.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们最终会分开\N{\rENG}going to break up eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.39,0:41:41.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问\N{\rENG}Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.35,0:41:43.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你的父母还在一起吗  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Are your parents are still together?  - No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.97,0:41:45.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有 那你的呢\N{\rENG}No and what about yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.22,0:41:47.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,在一起 但他们可以离婚\N{\rENG}They are, but they could divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.82,0:41:50.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们有钱的话\N{\rENG}I think if they had more money,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.23,0:41:51.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,估计早就离了\N{\rENG}they would not still be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.74,0:41:53.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,老天 你们都太实际了\N{\rENG}God, you guys are so practical,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.76,0:41:56.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真是生错了年代\N{\rENG}I was born into the wrong generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.38,0:41:58.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾祖母\N{\rENG}My grandmother's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.36,0:41:59.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,在她临终前\N{\rENG}wrote to our whole family
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.98,0:42:03.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,留下了二十六页的长信\N{\rENG}a 26-page letter from her deathbed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.05,0:42:04.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,她花了三页去说\N{\rENG}and she spent three pages
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.74,0:42:06.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,她为一部戏设计的服装\N{\rENG}on the costume she did for a play...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.90,0:42:08.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,而仅用一段来说她的丈夫\N{\rENG}and only one paragraph on her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.68,0:42:09.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,她也是演员吗\N{\rENG}Was she an actress too?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.80,0:42:11.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 她是个\N{\rENG}No... she was...a...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.28,0:42:14.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,英语“女裁缝”怎么说\N{\rENG}Comment on dit " couturière "?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.40,0:42:16.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,女裁缝\N{\rENG}Seamstress.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.53,0:42:18.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,她有很多\N{\rENG}And she had all these
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.36,0:42:22.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,不错的朋友 而关于我曾祖父\N{\rENG}wonderful friends and about my great-grandfather
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.19,0:42:24.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,她仅提到三件事\N{\rENG}She mentioned three events:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.01,0:42:26.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,他去参战 因为他的工作搬家\N{\rENG}He went to war, we moved because of his job
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.73,0:42:28.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,他死了\N{\rENG}And he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:31.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的忠告是\N{\rENG}Her big advice was
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.14,0:42:33.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要在浪漫的爱情上消耗太多\N{\rENG}not to be too consumed with romantic love
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.93,0:42:36.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,友谊和工作\N{\rENG}Friendships and work, she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.01,0:42:38.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,才给我带来真正的快乐\N{\rENG}brought to her the most happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:39.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我再同意不过了\N{\rENG}I could not agree more,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.70,0:42:42.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们就是被这样教育长大的 对吧\N{\rENG}I mean that's the thing that fucks us up right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.28,0:42:44.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,只有这种精神伴侣\N{\rENG}This idea of a soul mate of someone
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.78,0:42:46.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,才能让我们变得完整\N{\rENG}who would come to complete us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.62,0:42:49.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,帮助我们承担生活中的问题\N{\rENG}and save us from having to take care of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.89,0:42:53.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于斯特凡诺斯 我将标准降得非常低\N{\rENG}With Stefanos, I set the bar extremely low
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.92,0:42:56.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道他做不到我的要求\N{\rENG}I know he is not gonna meet any of my needs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.21,0:42:57.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,太难了\N{\rENG}Definitely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.26,0:43:00.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,那你的祖母呢 她是你的精神伴侣吗\N{\rENG}So what about Grandma? Was she your soul mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.49,0:43:02.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,说得好听 不过\N{\rENG}Sounds appealing but actually
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.12,0:43:04.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,你祖母其实更加理性一些\N{\rENG}your grandmother was more rational than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.49,0:43:07.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,她很独立 也这样要求我\N{\rENG}She took cared of herself and asked me to do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.75,0:43:09.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我们有足够的空间 协商一致\N{\rENG}With plenty of room to meet in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.66,0:43:11.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,听起来很理想\N{\rENG}Yeah, that sounds ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.17,0:43:12.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,那确实很理想\N{\rENG}That's is, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.94,0:43:15.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,很显然 我妻子今天不在这\N{\rENG}But it must be obvious that my wife is not here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.69,0:43:17.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们从来不是一个人\N{\rENG}We were never one person,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.31,0:43:20.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,是两个独立的人 我们也很喜欢这样\N{\rENG}always two, we preferred it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.04,0:43:21.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是美丽的故事\N{\rENG}That is so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.36,0:43:23.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为我的丈夫\N{\rENG}I think my husband is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.27,0:43:26.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是想吞并我\N{\rENG}always trying to almost colonize me, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.96,0:43:28.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我吞并你吗\N{\rENG}I colonize you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.77,0:43:32.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 但我也在吞并你 亲爱的\N{\rENG}Yes but I colonize you, too, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.63,0:43:34.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Well ... Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.14,0:43:36.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,但在最后的时日\N{\rENG}But at the end of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.13,0:43:37.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会发现\N{\rENG}It's not the love of one
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.90,0:43:40.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不是爱着一个人 而是爱着这种生活\N{\rENG}other person that matters it's the love of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.75,0:43:41.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,那太好了 帕特里克\N{\rENG}That's good to know, Patrick,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.81,0:43:43.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为生活我能自己掌控\N{\rENG}because life I can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.69,0:43:45.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,而阿里阿德涅\N{\rENG}Ariadni, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.57,0:43:47.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们都知道希腊出悲剧 对吧\N{\rENG}We all know that the Greeks invented tragedy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.73,0:43:48.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且她还来自玛尼\N{\rENG}and on top of that it stems
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.78,0:43:53.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,狂躁这个词就来源于此地\N{\rENG}from the original Mani, which is short for Mania.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.91,0:44:01.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,对了 如果今晚我们去不了旅馆\N{\rENG}Hey, guys if we can not make that hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.00,0:44:03.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们能退掉它或你们自己去住吗\N{\rENG}room tonight could you get a refund or use it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.85,0:44:05.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 我们退不了款\N{\rENG}No... we do not get a refund.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.43,0:44:07.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们不想住吗\N{\rENG}Are you trying to get out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.82,0:44:09.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 这份礼物太棒了\N{\rENG}No, it's such a great gift you've given us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.40,0:44:11.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,但还要打行李\N{\rENG}But I'm so stressed getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.05,0:44:13.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有女孩们 压力太大\N{\rENG}all the packing ready, with the girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.32,0:44:14.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不 不  - 这样吧\N{\rENG}- No, no...  - We made a deal guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.22,0:44:16.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们帮你看孩子 你们好好享受\N{\rENG}We will watch the kids, you're gonna love it.
