Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.29,0:44:22.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那感觉非常美妙 你们不会后悔的  - 没错\N{\rENG}- the hotel You won't regret it.  - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.57,0:44:25.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,不去的话 我们可是会生气的\N{\rENG}And we would be very offended if you don't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.17,0:44:26.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.19,0:44:27.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你们\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.21,0:44:32.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我想起我的丈夫\N{\rENG}Well... when I think of my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.21,0:44:34.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我非常想念\N{\rENG}what I miss the most about him
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.12,0:44:38.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,夜晚他躺在我身边的感觉\N{\rENG}is the way he used to lie down next to me at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.69,0:44:42.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时他会把胳膊横在我的胸前\N{\rENG}Sometimes his arm would stretch along my chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.76,0:44:47.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我动不了 甚至要憋住呼吸\N{\rENG}and I could not move, I... I even held my breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.33,0:44:51.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我感到 安心\N{\rENG}But I felt safe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.25,0:44:52.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,完整\N{\rENG}Complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.87,0:44:55.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也想念\N{\rENG}And... I miss the way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.47,0:44:58.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,他走在街上吹着口哨的样子\N{\rENG}he was whistling walking down the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.81,0:45:02.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,每次做什么我都会想他怎么做\N{\rENG}And every time I do something I think of what he would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.40,0:45:05.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,天冷了 要披上围巾\N{\rENG}when it's cold today, wear a scarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.10,0:45:11.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是之后 我渐渐忘却细节\N{\rENG}But lately I've been forgetting little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.31,0:45:16.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,记忆在不断褪色 我开始忘记他\N{\rENG}It's sort of fading and I'm starting to forget him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.22,0:45:18.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就像\N{\rENG}And it's like ...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.78,0:45:22.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我又失去了他\N{\rENG}like losing him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.58,0:45:26.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以有时 我努力回想\N{\rENG}So sometimes I make myself remember
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.24,0:45:28.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,他脸庞的每一处\N{\rENG}every detail of his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.75,0:45:32.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,眼睛的颜色 唇齿的样子\N{\rENG}The exact color of his eyes, his lips, his teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.91,0:45:36.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的皮肤和头发的触感\N{\rENG}the texture of his skin, his hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.13,0:45:40.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一切记忆都随着时间流走了\N{\rENG}That was all gone by the time he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.06,0:45:44.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,但有时 偶尔 只是偶尔\N{\rENG}And sometimes... not always, but sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.63,0:45:46.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能非常清楚的看到他\N{\rENG}I can actually see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.98,0:45:49.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,就好像拨开云雾 他就在那里\N{\rENG}It's as if a cloud moves away and there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.65,0:45:51.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我几乎能碰到他\N{\rENG}And I could almost touch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.62,0:45:55.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,突然 真实回到了眼前\N{\rENG}But then... the real world rushes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.76,0:45:58.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,他再次消失了\N{\rENG}And he vanishes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.79,0:46:01.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,曾几何时 每天早晨\N{\rENG}For a while, I did this every morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.25,0:46:03.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,天刚亮的时候 我都会看到他\N{\rENG}when the sun was not too bright outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.94,0:46:07.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,可不知为何 他又会消失在阳光下\N{\rENG}But the sun somehow makes him vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.32,0:46:11.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,他出现又消失\N{\rENG}And he appears and he disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.78,0:46:14.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,像日出和日落\N{\rENG}like a sunrise and a sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.90,0:46:18.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,一切都那么短暂\N{\rENG}Anything, so ephemeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.81,0:46:21.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,正如我们的生活\N{\rENG}It's just like our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.37,0:46:26.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们出现又消失\N{\rENG}We appear and we disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.14,0:46:29.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们对有些人来说很重要\N{\rENG}And we are so important to some,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.73,0:46:33.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我们又只是擦肩而过\N{\rENG}but we are just... passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.42,0:46:38.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,敬 擦肩而过\N{\rENG}To "passing through"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.80,0:46:43.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,敬 擦肩而过\N{\rENG}To "Passing through"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.01,0:46:55.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,终于 他在窗户的倒映下看清了自己的脸\N{\rENG}And eventually he catches his face in the window's reflection
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.65,0:46:57.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,他意识到自己已不再是那个9岁的小男孩了\N{\rENG}And he realizes he's no longer a 9 year old boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.96,0:46:59.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,对吧 他突然之间变老了 有了胡子\N{\rENG}Right? He's suddenly old, he's got a beard
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.89,0:47:02.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 眼睛里水雾缭绕  - 确实让人难过\N{\rENG}- and his eyes are watery  - This one seems sad
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.88,0:47:04.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,开始我还以为你要给我讲故事\N{\rENG}At first I thought you were going to tell me a story
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.59,0:47:06.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是关于一个人臆想出一个朋友的那个\N{\rENG}about a guy that has an imaginary friend
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.45,0:47:07.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,哪个\N{\rENG}Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.11,0:47:10.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,他五十多岁的时候 那个虚拟朋友又出现了\N{\rENG}When in his 50s, the imaginary  friend shows up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.43,0:47:11.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,和一只蜂鸟一起\N{\rENG}With the hummingbird?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.49,0:47:13.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错 就是这个  - 你喜欢吗\N{\rENG}- Yes, that!  - You liked that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.35,0:47:14.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,很有趣\N{\rENG}It's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.64,0:47:16.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,还记得你让我看过的那封信吗\N{\rENG}Remember that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.27,0:47:18.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你二十岁时写给\N{\rENG}that you let me read that you wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.42,0:47:20.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,四十岁的自己的那封信\N{\rENG}when you were 20 to yourself at 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.51,0:47:21.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然 我还记得第一句话\N{\rENG}Yes, I remember the first sentence:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.68,0:47:24.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,亲爱的四十岁的杰西 但愿你没有离婚\N{\rENG}Dear 40-year-old Jesse, I hope you're not divorced
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.28,0:47:25.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不记得有这部分了\N{\rENG}No I did not even remember that part,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.81,0:47:28.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是想说那封信里还提到别的事情\N{\rENG}I meant to all the other things in that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.15,0:47:31.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还是那个你 我们总觉得自己会成长\N{\rENG}You're the same guy, I mean, we always think that we are evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.59,0:47:33.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我们并无力改变多少\N{\rENG}But we can not change that much
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.64,0:47:35.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你知道我是怎样看待我的变化的  - 怎样\N{\rENG}- You know how I think I've changed the most.  - How?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.75,0:47:38.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我年轻的时候总希望时间可以过得快一点\N{\rENG}When I was younger I just wanted time to speed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.55,0:47:39.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rENG}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.40,0:47:42.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为那样 我就可以做我自己\N{\rENG}So I can be on my own, so I can be free from my parents
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.24,0:47:43.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,摆脱掉家长和学校的一切束缚\N{\rENG}and school and all that shit, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.47,0:47:46.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我希望自己闭上眼 一睁眼就变成了成年人\N{\rENG}I just wanted to close my eyes and wake up and be an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.81,0:47:48.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在一切都如我所愿成为现实\N{\rENG}And now I can feel that that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.29,0:47:50.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我却希望时间能停下来\N{\rENG}and I want everything to slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.37,0:47:51.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,很奇怪 在我的一生当中\N{\rENG}It's strange I've always had
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.64,0:47:54.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种感觉始终挥之不去\N{\rENG}this feeling no matter where I am in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.06,0:47:56.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,既像是真实存在 又仿佛南柯一梦\N{\rENG}That it's either a memory or a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.09,0:47:58.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道你一直有这种感觉\N{\rENG}I know you've always thought that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.21,0:48:00.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是 就好像 这真的是我的人生吗\N{\rENG}Me too, it's like is this really my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.51,0:48:02.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在这一切都正在发生吗\N{\rENG}Like is it happening, right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.35,0:48:04.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 就是这样  - 我知道\N{\rENG}- It is.  - I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.45,0:48:06.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,每一年 我都会感受到\N{\rENG}Every year I just seem to get
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.81,0:48:07.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,更大的压力和打击\N{\rENG}a little bit more humbled and more overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.96,0:48:10.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,那些事情我从来搞不明白\N{\rENG}about all things I'm never gonna know or understand
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.54,0:48:11.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是我一直在告诫你的\N{\rENG}That's what I keep telling you:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.51,0:48:12.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一无所知\N{\rENG}You know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.22,0:48:14.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 我已经醒悟了\N{\rENG}I know, I know! I'm coming around!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.56,0:48:16.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实 一无所知并没有你想象的那么糟糕\N{\rENG}But not knowing is not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.50,0:48:17.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说\N{\rENG}I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.76,0:48:20.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,关键是要不断发现 寻找\N{\rENG}The point is to be looking, searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.97,0:48:22.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,保持如饥似渴的状态\N{\rENG}to stay hungry, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.11,0:48:24.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 我只是希望能变得简单一点\N{\rENG}That's true... I just wish it was a little easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.56,0:48:26.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么意思\N{\rENG}How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.26,0:48:29.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道的 就是保持一定的热情\N{\rENG}Just to maintain a certain level of passion, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.16,0:48:31.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的一切都那么顺理成章\N{\rENG}I mean, it used to come so naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.95,0:48:34.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,记得我年轻的时候 我的一群作家朋友们\N{\rENG}Remember when I was younger, me and all my writer friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.58,0:48:37.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们可以感觉到自己在做的是重要的事情\N{\rENG}We like.. we just felt like were doing something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.43,0:48:39.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 就好像是属于我们的时代\N{\rENG}You know? Like this was our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.10,0:48:41.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,可他们都是些骄傲自大的小子 对吗\N{\rENG}But they were all a bunch of arrogant little pricks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.93,0:48:44.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 好吧 也许吧 我也不知道\N{\rENG}No! Alright, maybe... I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.21,0:48:45.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们长大后就渐渐失去了\N{\rENG}we just grew out of all this energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.92,0:48:49.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,当初的热情 创造力和雄心壮志\N{\rENG}all this creativity or whatever ambitions people had.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.86,0:48:54.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得人还是应该年少轻狂些才好\N{\rENG}I think you gotta be a little deluded to stay motivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.05,0:48:57.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,年轻人都是这样 不停地把自己和别人比较\N{\rENG}Young men have this thing about comparing themselves all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.28,0:49:00.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们有很多自我评判的准绳\N{\rENG}They have all these signposts they judge themselves by.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.68,0:49:01.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以前也是这样\N{\rENG}You used to do that all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.78,0:49:02.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我怎么了 你什么意思\N{\rENG}Do what? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.81,0:49:05.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,像巴尔扎克十七岁创作出这部作品\N{\rENG}It's like Balzac wrote this by 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.70,0:49:06.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,而斯科特 ·菲茨杰拉德三十岁才写出来\N{\rENG}F. Scott Fitzgerald did this by 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.99,0:49:09.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,巴尔扎克每天早餐前创作一部作品\N{\rENG}And Balzac wrote a book before breakfast everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.20,0:49:12.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 可是女人们并不这么想\N{\rENG}Yeah, but women do not think that way as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.38,0:49:13.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这么认为吗\N{\rENG}You don't think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.55,0:49:16.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们只是没什么可比的罢了\N{\rENG}We have much less to compare ourselves to, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.41,0:49:18.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,大多数有所成就的女人\N{\rENG}Most women who achieve anything in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.68,0:49:20.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你第一次听说她们时 都已经五十多岁了\N{\rENG}the first time you hear about them, they're in their 50s.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.85,0:49:21.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为在这以前 对女人来说\N{\rENG}because it is was so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.77,0:49:24.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,想要得到一定的社会地位实在是太难了\N{\rENG}for them to get any recognitions before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.19,0:49:25.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们要么苦苦奋斗了三十年\N{\rENG}They struggled for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.83,0:49:28.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,要么就是在能做自己想做的事之前\N{\rENG}or they raised kids and were stranded at home
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.64,0:49:30.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,都被困在家里 相夫教子\N{\rENG}before they could do what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.63,0:49:34.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 这其实也算是一种解放\N{\rENG}Actually you know what? It's kind of freeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.44,0:49:35.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不用每天忙着去和马丁·路德·金\N{\rENG}We don't have to spend our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.71,0:49:39.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,圣雄甘地 托尔斯泰这些人去比较\N{\rENG}comparing ourselves to Martin Luther King, Ghandi, Tolstoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.91,0:49:41.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,那圣女贞德呢\N{\rENG}What about Joan of Arc?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.22,0:49:44.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 她一个小姑娘却拯救了法国\N{\rENG}I mean... she was a teenager and she saved France.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.74,0:49:47.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁愿意做圣女贞德 忘记法国吧\N{\rENG}Who wants to be Joan of Arc? Forget France.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.45,0:49:50.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,她被绑在火刑柱上活活烧死 还是处女呢\N{\rENG}She was burned at the stake, and a virgin!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.25,0:49:53.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可不想这样 好吗 多伟大的情操\N{\rENG}Ok? Nothing I aspire to. What a great achievement!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.64,0:49:59.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 天哪  - 怎么了  - 没什么\N{\rENG}- Oh God...  - What?  - No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.50,0:50:01.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了  - 这太奇怪了\N{\rENG}- What?  - This is so weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.38,0:50:08.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么意思  - 就像这样 我们边走边聊\N{\rENG}- What do you mean?  - Just this, us walking, having a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.89,0:50:12.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,讨论一切和饮食工作无关的话题\N{\rENG}About something else than scheduling food, work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.10,0:50:12.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从为一些鸡毛蒜皮的事劳心后\N{\rENG}I mean how long has it been
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.89,0:50:15.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们确实很久没有像现在这样了\N{\rENG}since we were wondering around bullshiting
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.34,0:50:18.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我听到了什么 你能听到吗\N{\rENG}Do you hear what I hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.97,0:50:21.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 大海的声音吗  - 不\N{\rENG}- The sea?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.15,0:50:24.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么 我知道了 没琐事牵绊的声音\N{\rENG}What? Oh! No small feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.02,0:50:27.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有什么被推翻 没有什么需要清理\N{\rENG}Nothing being knocked over, nothing we have clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.63,0:50:29.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,也没有什么不公正的事情发生\N{\rENG}Nothing injustices being done.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.86,0:50:32.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,对啊 上一次是什么时候呢\N{\rENG}Yeah, so when was the last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.49,0:50:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我们无处可去的时候\N{\rENG}When we had nowhere to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.00,0:50:39.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 还记得我们在卢森堡公园吗\N{\rENG}Yeah. Remember walking around the Luxembourg Gardens?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.29,0:50:41.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在混凝土乒乓球桌上把你打得落花流水\N{\rENG}I used to kick your ass in ping-pong on those concrete tables
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.81,0:50:44.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,恭喜你 竟然打赢了个怀着双胞胎的孕妇\N{\rENG}Congrats! You beat a woman pregnant with twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.85,0:50:45.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,真够男人的\N{\rENG}Such a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.73,0:50:47.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,这总比输给一个怀着双胞胎的孕妇要好\N{\rENG}It is better than losing to a pregnant woman with twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.93,0:50:49.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 天哪\N{\rENG}Yes... O God!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.17,0:50:51.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我在想什么吗 我在想\N{\rENG}You know what I think? I think
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.20,0:50:54.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,从我们离开父母的那一刻起\N{\rENG}it's from the time we leave our parents' house,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.67,0:50:56.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到我们有了孩子\N{\rENG}until we have kids, that's the only time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.63,0:50:58.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,只有那时 你的生活是完全属于你自己的\N{\rENG}that your life is completely your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.78,0:51:01.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,那种日子大概过了十年 真的很好\N{\rENG}I think I had about a decade of that, it was great, it was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.53,0:51:04.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像是一次漫长的流浪 每一天\N{\rENG}just like one long flowing, a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.51,0:51:06.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,一星期 一年 都没有太大的区别\N{\rENG}a week, a year, there wasn't much difference
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.84,0:51:09.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 我过去总是把时间\N{\rENG}No... I know, I used to keep track of time
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.03,0:51:11.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,花在工作和男朋友们的身上\N{\rENG}through jobs and boyfriends and stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.81,0:51:12.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我却可以说出\N{\rENG}Now I can tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.71,0:51:15.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,在过去的七年中\N{\rENG}every detail of the past seven years
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.18,0:51:17.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,孩子们身上发生过的每一件小事\N{\rENG}based on what was happening in the girls' lives
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.04,0:51:18.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 没错\N{\rENG}Yeah...right... totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.40,0:51:21.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你也是吗  - 是的\N{\rENG}- You do that too?  - Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.33,0:51:23.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 如果真的把时间划分开\N{\rENG}if, I mean, time is demarcated now
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.93,0:51:26.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 真不敢相信 你竟然也记得\N{\rENG}No, I'm just surprised you do that too
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.97,0:51:29.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 来个小测验\N{\rENG}Ok... quick test
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.35,0:51:31.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,二〇〇九年八月\N{\rENG}August 2009.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.39,0:51:35.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧 考考你 那时发生了什么\N{\rENG}No, come on! It's a quick one. What was happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.23,0:51:38.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,二〇〇九年八月 我们在和你父母度假\N{\rENG}August 2009, we were on vacation with your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.86,0:51:41.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,妮娜先起了水痘 紧接着就是艾拉\N{\rENG}Nina got the chickenpox first and quickly followed by Ella
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.79,0:51:45.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真没想到  - 可以奖励我一颗五角星了吗\N{\rENG}- I am so impressed.  - So do I get a gold star?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.59,0:51:46.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以考虑\N{\rENG}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.26,0:51:50.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我能问你一个问题吗  - 当然了\N{\rENG}- Hey... can I ask you a question?  - Sure.
