Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.80,0:59:18.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,来看看 有人吗\N{\rENG}Check this out! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.24,0:59:24.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是圣奥蒂莉亚的神龛 她是视力的守护神\N{\rENG}It's a shrine to St. Odilia, the patron saint to eyesight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.99,0:59:25.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们从各处前来\N{\rENG}People come from all over
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.97,0:59:28.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,给盲人留下各种小贡品\N{\rENG}and they leave little dedications to the blind
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.15,0:59:30.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,帮助他们恢复视力\N{\rENG}to help restore sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.71,0:59:32.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,一定很灵吧\N{\rENG}I'm sure, it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.51,0:59:34.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,这里的这些画\N{\rENG}And these paitings here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.21,0:59:36.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我联想到日本的和尚\N{\rENG}they make me think of those Japanese monks, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.82,0:59:38.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有他们的无常思想\N{\rENG}with their deal on impermanence?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.37,0:59:40.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,天热时 他们喜欢用水在石头上画画\N{\rENG}They like to paint with water on rock on hot days
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.99,0:59:43.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以画完的时候 就都蒸发了\N{\rENG}so by the time they're done it's already evaporated.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.12,0:59:46.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,眼睛被挖掉了 是和失明有关吗\N{\rENG}Oh, the eyes are scratched out is that about blindness?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.68,0:59:47.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 我本来也那么想\N{\rENG}No, I thought that too,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.80,0:59:49.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是那个看守人\N{\rENG}but the caretaker guy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.87,0:59:53.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,他告诉我 是土耳其人占领的时候干的\N{\rENG}he told me that the Turks did that during the occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.13,0:59:57.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 我再也不吃土耳其食物了\N{\rENG}That's it. I'm never eating Turkish food again.
