Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.50,1:10:30.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么不让我和他说话\N{\rENG}Why can't I talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.58,1:10:31.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,你已经第二次这样了\N{\rENG}That's twice you've done that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.66,1:10:33.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,你完全可以把手机给我的\N{\rENG}Come on, you could have just handed me the phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.13,1:10:34.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我很想和他聊聊\N{\rENG}You know I wanted to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.21,1:10:36.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没时间多聊 他说他们在登机了\N{\rENG}Well he didn't have time to talk. He said they were boarding.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.48,1:10:37.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,他是什么忘带了 什么东西\N{\rENG}What did he forget? What was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.71,1:10:40.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的科学项目报告 我们明天就去寄\N{\rENG}His science project, but we'll mail it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.77,1:10:43.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他没事的  - 你不该那样说他妈妈\N{\rENG}- He'll be fine  - You shouldn't have said that about his mom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.76,1:10:45.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么 我说什么了\N{\rENG}What? What did I say?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.30,1:10:47.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,和你妈妈相处愉快\N{\rENG}"Good luck with your mom."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.24,1:10:49.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 拜托  - 我可没别的意思\N{\rENG}- I mean, c'mon...  - I  didn't mean anything by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.68,1:10:51.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 但这样不好\N{\rENG}I know, but it's not good.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.11,1:10:52.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样又让他想起了整件事情\N{\rENG}You know, it just reminds him of the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.54,1:10:53.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真希望你别那样\N{\rENG}and I wish you wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.57,1:10:55.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为我不说他就忘了吗\N{\rENG}Oh, like you think he forgets?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.23,1:10:56.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是典型的美式思维\N{\rENG}That's so American
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.03,1:10:58.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,掩盖事实 当做从未发生\N{\rENG}to just swipe it under the carpet and act as if it didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.57,1:11:00.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 为什么要让他想起来呢\N{\rENG}Why put it into his head, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.35,1:11:02.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许他这会儿不想去想这件事呢\N{\rENG}What if he does not want to think about it right now?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.54,1:11:06.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不会有影响的  - 会有一点 会的\N{\rENG}- It means nothing.  - It means something. It does.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.87,1:11:08.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 前些天我还和他开了个玩笑\N{\rENG}Alright, I even made a joke the other day
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.63,1:11:09.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,说我和他妈妈应该\N{\rENG}that his mom and I should try
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.87,1:11:12.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,来一场泥地大摔跤 才能一决胜负\N{\rENG}to settle it in one big mud wrestling contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.59,1:11:15.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 泥地大摔跤 你真那么说了  - 他笑了\N{\rENG}- Mud wrestling? You said that?  - And he laughed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.37,1:11:17.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许他比你要有幽默感\N{\rENG}He might have more of a sense of humour than you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.32,1:11:18.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托\N{\rENG}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.37,1:11:19.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们刚说过的\N{\rENG}I dunno, we just talked about that,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.98,1:11:21.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说他妈妈坏话的时候\N{\rENG}you know, when you say bad things about his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.68,1:11:23.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,他听见的是自己的坏话\N{\rENG}what he hears is bad things about himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.63,1:11:26.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可没说他妈妈坏话 我开个玩笑而已\N{\rENG}Well I didn't say anything bad about his mom, ok? I made a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.06,1:11:28.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,开的不光是她的玩笑 也是我自己的\N{\rENG}It's as much on me as much as it is on her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.25,1:11:32.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 我知道 只是 根本没必要提\N{\rENG}I know, I know. It's just why conjure it up at all, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.66,1:11:34.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得他现在够大了\N{\rENG}I think he's old enough now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.33,1:11:37.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,他知道他妈妈和我之间是怎么回事\N{\rENG}I mean, he knows how bad it is between his mother and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.66,1:11:39.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是他妈妈和我  - 我什么也没做\N{\rENG}- His mom and me.  - And I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.65,1:11:41.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,都是她冲着我来的\N{\rENG}It's all coming from her towards me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.41,1:11:45.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,她恨我 没错 很久前我睡了她男人\N{\rENG}OK, she hates me. Yes. I fucked her husband a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.26,1:11:47.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者是不是该说 他睡了我\N{\rENG}Or should I say he fucked me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.63,1:11:48.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 没错\N{\rENG}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.82,1:11:50.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈妈和我本来就不和\N{\rENG}Ok, making a joke about the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.65,1:11:53.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,拿这开个玩笑 没什么大不了的\N{\rENG}that his mother and I do not love each other is not the issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.35,1:11:54.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不会因为这样就受到创伤\N{\rENG}That's not going to traumatize him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.98,1:11:56.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为他已经受伤了 好吗\N{\rENG}That already happened, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.58,1:11:59.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在你想转移你的负罪感给我吗\N{\rENG}And now you are trying to transfer your guilt and blame me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.34,1:12:00.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.92,1:12:03.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗 反过来 如果你能一笑了之\N{\rENG}You know, on the contrary, if you can make a joke about it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.05,1:12:04.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许你就能好受点\N{\rENG}maybe you'll be able to live with it better.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.54,1:12:06.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是这么想的  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- That's what I think.  - OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.19,1:12:08.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说得对 一如既往\N{\rENG}You're right, as always.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.75,1:12:10.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们别说这个了 好吗\N{\rENG}Let's just not talk about it, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.63,1:12:13.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈妈要是个醉鬼\N{\rENG}It's nobody's fault if his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.55,1:12:15.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者虐待狂 可怨不得任何人\N{\rENG}is drunk and abusive psychologically.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.85,1:12:17.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,别那么说\N{\rENG}Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.64,1:12:20.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,他得和她一起生活 想到这我就恶心\N{\rENG}I mean it makes me sick that he has to be with her
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.07,1:12:23.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我想 法官会认为女人都有母性吧\N{\rENG}but I guess judges assume that women have the mother instinct.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.44,1:12:26.27,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}美狄亚{\u0}：希腊神话中科尔喀斯国王之女，以巫术著称\N{\rCHS}她的母性就和美狄亚差不多\N{\rENG}She has the mother instinct of Medea!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.56,1:12:27.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,美狄亚吗\N{\rENG}Medea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.98,1:12:29.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 那不过是个希腊神话\N{\rENG}Yeah, after all it is a Greek myth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.66,1:12:31.82,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}欧里庇得斯{\u0}：希腊悲剧诗人\N{\rCHS}其实是欧里庇得斯的剧作\N{\rENG}Actually, a play by Euripides.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.32,1:12:35.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个女人 为惩罚前夫不惜杀死孩子\N{\rENG}A woman killing her kids to punish her ex-husband,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.20,1:12:36.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,她和这没什么两样\N{\rENG}that's basically what she's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.35,1:12:37.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,她是在伤害他来报复你\N{\rENG}She's hurting him to get to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.96,1:12:40.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 她是利用他来破坏我的生活\N{\rENG}No, she's making my life hell through him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.53,1:12:41.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,这才是她所做的\N{\rENG}That's what she's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.86,1:12:46.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,但有时候 你说的话太过分了\N{\rENG}But sometimes you say things that just go too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.09,1:12:48.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,行了 别把你老婆的这个闹剧里\N{\rENG}Ok, stop blaming me for everything that is wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.26,1:12:49.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的问题都怪在我身上 好吗\N{\rENG}in this whole thing with your wife, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.92,1:12:53.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是前妻 很久以前就是前妻了  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- Ex-wife! Ex-wife for a long time!  - OK,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.06,1:12:54.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,你当初就应该处理得好一点\N{\rENG}you should have dealt better with it a little better back then,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.72,1:12:56.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,她就不会这么恨我们了\N{\rENG}she wouldn't have hated us so much, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.73,1:12:59.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 好 是我搞砸了\N{\rENG}OK, ok, I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.45,1:13:02.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真是厉害 我们生活中\N{\rENG}Alright. I just love this little rewrite you do that
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.57,1:13:06.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,有什么不如意 你都能说成是我的错\N{\rENG}everything that isn't perfect in our life gets laid at my feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.43,1:13:09.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在你要因为亨利 给我扣这种帽子吗\N{\rENG}Now you're putting this shit on me about Henry?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.24,1:13:12.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么帽子 你说什么呢\N{\rENG}What shit? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.66,1:13:14.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你我在说什么吧\N{\rENG}Let me tell you what I am talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.34,1:13:17.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这是要我搬去芝加哥 放弃我的生活\N{\rENG}The moving to Chicago and giving up my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.93,1:13:21.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说亨利需要你\N{\rENG}Now that you mentioned that Henry needs you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.35,1:13:23.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我什么感受吗\N{\rENG}how do you think that makes me feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.31,1:13:25.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很痛苦 知道吗\N{\rENG}I'm miserable, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.50,1:13:28.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还怎么接受那份工作 你告诉我\N{\rENG}How can I take that job now? Tell me, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.53,1:13:29.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我会有负罪感的  - 别这样\N{\rENG}- I'll feel too guilty.  - No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.79,1:13:31.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不行不行  - 那是你自己选择\N{\rENG}- No, no, no, no.  - That's a choice you're making
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.93,1:13:33.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,要这样看待它的 明白吗\N{\rENG}to look at it like that, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.41,1:13:37.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,女人就应该做养育者 这是天性\N{\rENG}It is in the nature of women to be the nurturer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.65,1:13:38.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rENG}The what?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.69,1:13:41.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 养育者  - 养育者\N{\rENG}- The nurturer.  - The nurturer?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.00,1:13:42.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 这个词我简直说不出口\N{\rENG}OK, I can't even say that fucking word.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.95,1:13:45.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就是本能地会对一切感到内疚\N{\rENG}I just naturally feel bad about everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.32,1:13:47.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还给我那种眼神 好像是我的错\N{\rENG}And you give me that look like it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.56,1:13:48.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么眼神\N{\rENG}What look?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.35,1:13:51.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是怪我忘了把项目报告放进包里的眼神\N{\rENG}That I forget to put in the bag the science project look.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.24,1:13:53.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我知道你怪我  - 我什么也没说\N{\rENG}- I know you blame me.  - I didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.52,1:13:55.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,对 你是什么也没说 你不用说出来\N{\rENG}No, you did not say anything. You didn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.97,1:13:59.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 错的从来都是我  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- Yeah, it's always my fault.  - Yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.80,1:14:01.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我上班时在冰箱上看到\N{\rENG}I read on the fridge at work,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.87,1:14:05.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,那种用来拼句子的 贴在磁铁上的单词\N{\rENG}you know those magnet words that people make sentences with.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.13,1:14:07.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,有人拼了这么个句子\N{\rENG}Someone had put together:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.61,1:14:13.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,在牺牲的花园里 女人寻求着永生\N{\rENG}"Women explore for eternity in the vast garden of sacrifice."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.24,1:14:17.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一定是上帝的指示吧\N{\rENG}Wow, that's a sure sign from God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.61,1:14:19.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 这话真他妈是真理\N{\rENG}Yeah, that line is so damn true
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.93,1:14:21.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,过去一万年来都是\N{\rENG}and it’s been for 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.39,1:14:22.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,但到此为止\N{\rENG}But that's enough, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.83,1:14:24.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不想做这样的女人\N{\rENG}I don't want to be one of these women.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.49,1:14:26.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像结婚权对于同性恋\N{\rENG}Like marriage is important to gays,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.53,1:14:28.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,避孕对于维护女权的重要性\N{\rENG}or contraception to women rights.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.56,1:14:30.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,一旦我失去了信心\N{\rENG}It's the same with giving up my hopes,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.46,1:14:31.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于无数妇女\N{\rENG}with the millions of women
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.54,1:14:32.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不得不放弃她们的希望\N{\rENG}that I have had to give up their hopes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.86,1:14:33.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会这样的\N{\rENG}I'm not gonna do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.87,1:14:36.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不是我一个人的事情\N{\rENG}This is bigger than me, this means more than me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.97,1:14:44.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,真精彩 连诺贝尔委员会都注意到了\N{\rENG}Wow, bravo, the Nobel Committee is taking note, and just...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.89,1:14:47.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,等下 我去通知一下瑞典方面 好吧\N{\rENG}Hold on a second, I'm going to alert Sweden, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.20,1:14:49.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,面对如此多的女性压迫问题\N{\rENG}I mean... it must be a full-time job
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.43,1:14:50.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一定是身负重任\N{\rENG}carrying that much feminine oppression.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.81,1:14:53.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错  - 遭受了这么多\N{\rENG}- It is.  - You suffered so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.10,1:14:54.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,在巴黎中产阶级家庭长大\N{\rENG}growing up in middle class Paris,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.60,1:14:56.60,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}后女性主义{\u0}：上世纪九十年代女性追求性认同的主义\N{\rCHS}在后女性主义者时期\N{\rENG}I mean the agony in the trenches
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.60,1:14:58.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,因索邦主义而苦恼\N{\rENG}of the Sorbonne in the post-feminist era.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.57,1:14:59.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,实在无法想像\N{\rENG}I can not imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.93,1:15:01.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是个混蛋\N{\rENG}You're an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.62,1:15:02.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗 亲爱的\N{\rENG}You know what, sweetie?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.81,1:15:04.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,搬去芝加哥后\N{\rENG}When I move into Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.96,1:15:07.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一定要找到一套好房子\N{\rENG}I want to make sure we're able to find a nice house,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.85,1:15:09.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,缝制窗帘\N{\rENG}and I can sew the drapes,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.60,1:15:11.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,挑些搭配的床罩\N{\rENG}And pick matching bed covers...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.47,1:15:14.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你今晚就打算这样度过吗\N{\rENG}So this is how you now want to be spending this evening?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.35,1:15:16.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,一直说这些吗\N{\rENG}I mean, this is, this is what you wanna do tonight?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.09,1:15:16.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你先开始的  - 不\N{\rENG}- Well, you started it.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.98,1:15:20.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,是你一直念叨个不停\N{\rENG}You're the one who will not shut up about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.95,1:15:24.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,但如果真心想说 我是说谈论什么\N{\rENG}But if you want to talk about it, I mean really talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.16,1:15:28.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,那就心平气和 理性地说\N{\rENG}I would prefer to have an unemotional, rational conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.21,1:15:29.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们能做到吗\N{\rENG}I mean, do you think we could do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.27,1:15:31.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这可能吗  - 又开始了\N{\rENG}- Would that be possible?  - Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.46,1:15:33.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,要心平气和 要理性\N{\rENG}Unemotional, rational.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.28,1:15:36.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你总是那个理智的人\N{\rENG}You always play the part of the one and only rational one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.52,1:15:40.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我一直在不可理喻歇斯底里地闹\N{\rENG}And I'm the irrational, hysterical, hormone-crazy one,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.10,1:15:41.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,是因为我有感情\N{\rENG}because I have emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.53,1:15:44.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,是 你以旁观者从全局角度谈论问题\N{\rENG}Yeah, you sit back and you speak from your big perspective,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.58,1:15:47.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以你说出来的一定是经过冷静思考的\N{\rENG}which means everything you say is level-headed and true.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.20,1:15:49.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我也没有总是袖手旁观  - 整个世界\N{\rENG}- I don't always do anything.  - The world is fucked
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.33,1:15:52.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,都被冷静而理智的男人的决策给毁掉了\N{\rENG}by unemotional, irrational men deciding shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.39,1:15:55.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,政客无故就计划开战\N{\rENG}Alright? Politicians going to war for no reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.15,1:15:57.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,商业巨头要榨干能源\N{\rENG}corporate heads deciding to rape the environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.74,1:16:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,钱尼·拉姆斯菲尔德 多么理智的男人\N{\rENG}Chaney, Rumsfeld, very rational men.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.84,1:16:02.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,钱尼·拉姆斯菲尔德 那倒是\N{\rENG}Chaney, Rumsfeld, yeah, ok.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.51,1:16:03.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我知道解决办法\N{\rENG}If I know a solution,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.35,1:16:06.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,一定是经过深思熟虑才决定的\N{\rENG}Very rational thinking behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.20,1:16:09.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我们现在是怎样 挑战最终解决方案\N{\rENG}Okay, so we are there now? Us versus the final solution.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.39,1:16:12.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,行 这样 回答我一个问题好吧\N{\rENG}Okay... let's do it, alright? Let me ask you this, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.44,1:16:15.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得亨利的生活\N{\rENG}Do you think Henry's life
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.52,1:16:17.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,会不会因为你我关系更为稳定\N{\rENG}would be helped by more consistent presence
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.98,1:16:19.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,而有所改善\N{\rENG}by you and me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.00,1:16:20.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 又来了  - 不\N{\rENG}- Here we go.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.98,1:16:23.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不罢休 那就好好来谈谈 行不\N{\rENG}You won't drop it. So let's talk about it. Alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.41,1:16:25.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就问你一句\N{\rENG}Let me just ask you one question.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.80,1:16:28.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克会不会因为你我关系更为稳定\N{\rENG}Do you think Hank's life would be better served by
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.35,1:16:30.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,而在生活上得到更好的照顾\N{\rENG}more consistent presence from you and me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.57,1:16:32.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然 他跟我们住一起会更好\N{\rENG}Yes! I think it would be better if he lived with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.76,1:16:33.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对  - 而且他妈\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - And I think his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.75,1:16:36.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,是个酗酒又讨厌的贱人\N{\rENG}is a fucking alcoholic, hateful cunt
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.30,1:16:38.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,利用我们在巴黎 我在生孩子的时间\N{\rENG}that used the time we were in Paris and I was giving birth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.81,1:16:42.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,差点就把亨利合法驱逐出纽约\N{\rENG}and almost dying to legally move Henry out of New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.60,1:16:43.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,操丫的\N{\rENG}Fuck her!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.33,1:16:46.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 这我同意你\N{\rENG}Okay, I agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.60,1:16:49.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然遗憾的是 我们不能让他离开美国\N{\rENG}Okay, unfortunately we can not go and get him out of America,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.87,1:16:52.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,但可以在想去见他的时候过去\N{\rENG}but we could if we wanted to go to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.82,1:16:55.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然这是个大变动\N{\rENG}Now I know it would be a big move,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.31,1:16:56.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你还是考虑考虑如何\N{\rENG}but what do you think? I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.12,1:16:59.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,在美国就真的找不到让你开心的事情吗\N{\rENG}is there any way that you could be happy in the US?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.73,1:17:02.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,难道去美国就是不可能的事情吗\N{\rENG}I mean is that just out of the realm of possibility?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.16,1:17:04.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,也可以找一份差不多的工作的 是不是\N{\rENG}I mean you could find a comparable job there?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.77,1:17:06.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 差不多的  - 对啊\N{\rENG}- Comparable job?  - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.01,1:17:07.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你搞笑的吧  - 不\N{\rENG}- Are you kidding?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.54,1:17:09.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么总让我来妥协\N{\rENG}Why am I the one that always have to make the compromises?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.64,1:17:10.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.56,1:17:13.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不应该是  - 别搞这么夸张 好吗\N{\rENG}- I mean it should be...  - Don't be so dramatic, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.36,1:17:15.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我 反正要搬去芝加哥这事\N{\rENG}I... Well, moving to Chicago is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.01,1:17:17.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对我来说就是很夸张  - 我不是说\N{\rENG}- Pretty fucking dramatic to me.  - I'm not saying
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.59,1:17:20.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,就该搬过去 我只是想谈谈这可能性\N{\rENG}we should move. I just want to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.50,1:17:23.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就不能淡定那么两秒钟 好好谈谈吗\N{\rENG}Can you be my friend for like two seconds so we can talk?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.07,1:17:24.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 行 就一会儿  - 好的\N{\rENG}- Okay, two seconds  - Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.40,1:17:25.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,记不记得你有一次\N{\rENG}Do you remember that time that you were like
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.84,1:17:27.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,去接女儿们 迟到了大概三十五分钟\N{\rENG}35 minutes late to pick up the girls from school,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.82,1:17:29.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,你当时紧张死了\N{\rENG}and you were so stressed out,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.29,1:17:30.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为你知道她们在操场上\N{\rENG}because you knew they were out there in the playground,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.98,1:17:32.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,担心你是不是出什么事了\N{\rENG}wondering what the hell happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.94,1:17:35.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我 一直都有这种感觉\N{\rENG}Okay, that is the way that I feel all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.12,1:17:37.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我把自己的生活弄得一团糟\N{\rENG}You know, like I fucked up, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.74,1:17:40.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,之前一直没管他 现在我就想去接他\N{\rENG}I left him behind and I just want to go get him.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.62,1:17:42.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每次送他走就会这样\N{\rENG}You always get like this when you drop him off.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.99,1:17:45.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,你很失落 然后就开始跟我吵\N{\rENG}You're sad, so you start a fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.69,1:17:50.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没事的 他是个很棒的孩子 好吗\N{\rENG}He's fine, he's a great kid, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.77,1:17:53.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实就是他不再需要你像之前那样操心\N{\rENG}But the truth is that he does not need you the way he used to.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.69,1:17:55.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,你错过了可以陪伴\N{\rENG}You missed the opportunity to be with him
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.08,1:17:56.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他童年每一天的机会\N{\rENG}every day of his childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.22,1:17:57.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,已经错过了\N{\rENG}You just did.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.04,1:18:00.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,就算你再懊恼流泪 他也已经长大了\N{\rENG}And you can cry about it, but he is growing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.04,1:18:04.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,其他方面你是个很好的父亲\N{\rENG}You're a great father in other ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.65,1:18:07.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,离婚又不是什么稀奇事\N{\rENG}you got divorced like millions of other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.43,1:18:08.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,要说它适合吗 当然不是\N{\rENG}Was it ideal? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.97,1:18:10.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.58,1:18:11.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着\N{\rENG}Listen,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.37,1:18:14.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果一个月后你依旧想让我辞职\N{\rENG}if in one month, you still want me to quit my job,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.64,1:18:17.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我抛弃这些年积攒下的一切跟你走\N{\rENG}and give up everything I've been working towards all these years,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.30,1:18:18.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,直说就是了\N{\rENG}just ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.45,1:18:21.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,但现在我这个想法是一直都有的\N{\rENG}But right now I I feel the same way I always have.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.02,1:18:23.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可以搬回美国\N{\rENG}I would move back to the US
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.19,1:18:26.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,只要你的变态前妻能共享共同监护权\N{\rENG}if that diseased ex-wife of yours give us joint custody.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.36,1:18:29.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,但每隔一周的周末就会很难熬了 杰西\N{\rENG}But every other weekend amounts to shit, Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.09,1:18:31.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,一学期差不多就有三十天\N{\rENG}That's less than 30 days a semester,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.04,1:18:34.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我们为了那样的生活来放弃现在的日子\N{\rENG}and I don't think it's worth it for us to change our entire lives
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.00,1:18:35.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,是不值得的\N{\rENG}Over that kind of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.94,1:18:37.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你说的没错  - 是吧\N{\rENG}- I know you're right.  - Right, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.19,1:18:40.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,看 我倒成了理性的那个\N{\rENG}See? I'm being the rational one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.68,1:18:46.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是 汉克处境太糟 他是无辜的\N{\rENG}It's just... A shitty position. I mean Hank didn't do anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.37,1:18:48.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,可他却被一直忽略\N{\rENG}but he's the one getting kicked in the teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.03,1:18:51.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,人或多或少都会被父母的生活所拖累\N{\rENG}We all get dragged through our parent's lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.59,1:18:54.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不是我 你的婚姻又会是另种情况\N{\rENG}If it wasn't me, your marriage would have ended over something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.31,1:18:55.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这你很清楚  - 当然\N{\rENG}- And you know that.  - Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.79,1:18:57.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以他可能会被贫困家庭养育\N{\rENG}Or even worse he would have been raised
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.41,1:18:58.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,这更糟\N{\rENG}by two miserable parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.98,1:18:59.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rENG}Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.73,1:19:03.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真是生活一团糟啊\N{\rENG}I just really fucked that up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.55,1:19:09.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是说因为搬来巴黎和我在一起了吗\N{\rENG}You mean you fucked up by moving to Paris to be with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.30,1:19:10.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是  - 不\N{\rENG}- No...  - No,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.59,1:19:12.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我就知道代价太大  - 我不是…\N{\rENG}- I knew that was going to cost too much.  - That's not what I meant...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.38,1:19:14.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 停 我不是这意思  - 我就知道\N{\rENG}- Stop! That's not what I meant at all.  - I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.19,1:19:16.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我劝过你的 好吗  - 别说了\N{\rENG}- I told you not to do this, okay?  - Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.06,1:19:20.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 当初我抛下一切搬去纽约\N{\rENG}Okay... I moved to New York with you for two years,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.28,1:19:22.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,跟你住了两年\N{\rENG}and gave up everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.05,1:19:24.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我需要回来生孩子\N{\rENG}But I needed to be home to give birth to the twins,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.39,1:19:25.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为双胞胎生产太复杂\N{\rENG}because it was a complicated birth,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.69,1:19:28.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还想妈妈能陪我 你也是这样想的\N{\rENG}and I wanted to be with my mother and you wanted it, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.71,1:19:29.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对吧  - 是\N{\rENG}- Okay?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.47,1:19:31.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这是我唯一要求的事情  - 是\N{\rENG}- That's the one thing I asked from you.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.16,1:19:34.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,唯一一件 你就要因此永远责备我吗\N{\rENG}The one thing... and now you're gonna blame me forever?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.91,1:19:37.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,别说了 好吗\N{\rENG}Stop it, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.02,1:19:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,别说了\N{\rENG}Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.71,1:19:42.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你不想搬回美国 我们就不搬\N{\rENG}If you don't want to move back to the States, we won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.41,1:19:43.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,就不用再说了\N{\rENG}End of story.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.20,1:19:46.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 我只是在想\N{\rENG}Alright? I am just trying to find a way
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.52,1:19:49.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,究竟住在哪里 我的生活才能更稳定\N{\rENG}where I can be a more consistent presence in his life
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.13,1:19:52.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,能让他生活得更好 就像一家人一样\N{\rENG}and ideally I would like to do that as a family.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.11,1:19:54.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,不然你想分居还是离婚\N{\rENG}As a family or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.68,1:19:57.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,这他妈是怎么说起来的\N{\rENG}What the fuck does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.62,1:20:01.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能感受到你说的每个字\N{\rENG}I feel a passive-aggressive threat
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.68,1:20:02.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,都带有消极进攻的威胁\N{\rENG}in everything you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.96,1:20:07.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不这样 你就会怨我一辈子的\N{\rENG}Either do this or I will resent you for the rest of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.92,1:20:08.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,是不是\N{\rENG}No?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.95,1:20:11.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错吧\N{\rENG}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.21,1:20:16.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得…\N{\rENG}You know what? I'm sensing something...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.68,1:20:18.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,问题在于\N{\rENG}I, I, I think the problem is,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.42,1:20:21.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不想让我有一份稳定的工作\N{\rENG}is that you do not want me to have a more substantial job.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.44,1:20:23.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,从某种程度上来说\N{\rENG}On some level you feel threatened
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.41,1:20:25.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你因为我的成就而有威胁感\N{\rENG}by my achieving anything
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.22,1:20:27.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,在咱俩的关系中会削减你的地位\N{\rENG}that could diminish your status in our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.67,1:20:30.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在这段关系中的地位吗\N{\rENG}My status in our relationship?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.42,1:20:35.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我他妈在美国学校一学期教两门 好吗\N{\rENG}I teach two courses a semester at the fucking American school, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.05,1:20:37.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是有地位啊\N{\rENG}Wow, that's really some status!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.88,1:20:39.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你会在我有这样一个绝佳的\N{\rENG}No, no. I don't think it's any coincidence
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.34,1:20:41.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,工作机遇之时\N{\rENG}that you feel that way at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.20,1:20:43.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,却有那样的想法绝不是偶然\N{\rENG}that I have a truly exciting job opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.52,1:20:47.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,你很清楚 这一连串的都是你在瞎想\N{\rENG}This whole train of thought is complete horseshit and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.48,1:20:50.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我问你\N{\rENG}I have a question for you:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.90,1:20:54.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们没有女儿 还有这些有的没的\N{\rENG}If we didn't have the girls, all our crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.30,1:20:56.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们还会在一起吗\N{\rENG}Would we even still be together?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.28,1:20:57.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.47,1:21:00.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托 你他妈简直不可理喻\N{\rENG}I mean, you're the fucking mayor of the crazy town.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.10,1:21:01.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你自己也知道啊 不是吗\N{\rENG}Do you know that? You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.26,1:21:03.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得 你必须搬去芝加哥\N{\rENG}You know what I think? I think you have to move to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.82,1:21:04.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,亨利需要你\N{\rENG}I think Henry needs you,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.94,1:21:06.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我和女儿们就留在巴黎\N{\rENG}and I think I need to stay in Paris with the girls,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.71,1:21:07.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,接受这份工作\N{\rENG}and take this job.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.78,1:21:11.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你为什么要这样 简直不可理喻\N{\rENG}Why are you doing this? That's a ridiculous idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.26,1:21:13.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,要我离开你和女儿们 不行\N{\rENG}Like I'm gonna lose you and the girls? No!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.94,1:21:15.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,你干嘛把所有的事情都复杂化\N{\rENG}Why do you make everything so difficult?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.66,1:21:17.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰西 你跟我在一起并不快乐\N{\rENG}Jesse, you're unhappy with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.29,1:21:19.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怪我让你离开你的儿子\N{\rENG}You're blaming me for taking you away from your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.63,1:21:22.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这样说也太莫名了\N{\rENG}That is a completely irrational response
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.17,1:21:24.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是在理清我的思路\N{\rENG}to something I'm just trying to feel my way through.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.86,1:21:27.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着 杰西\N{\rENG}Listen, Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.79,1:21:30.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这一个半月里\N{\rENG}We just spent the last six weeks here,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.61,1:21:33.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们过得很开心\N{\rENG}and it's been great.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.29,1:21:36.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每天都能思如泉涌\N{\rENG}You've been able to write every day,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.38,1:21:39.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,天气也十分美好\N{\rENG}and the weather has been nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.32,1:21:42.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 但我之前并不想来希腊  - 我知道\N{\rENG}- But I didn't want to come to Greece.  - I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.13,1:21:45.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吧 你无法预料下一秒会发生什么\N{\rENG}Right? There could be a revolution any second.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.55,1:21:48.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们会吃掉很多羊乳酪和橄榄油\N{\rENG}People eat a lot of feta and olive oil.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.48,1:21:50.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,表面上看起来很开心\N{\rENG}And they act all happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.23,1:21:52.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,但实际谈论的却是自己受了多少气\N{\rENG}but they actually talk about how angry they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.64,1:21:53.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就犹豫了\N{\rENG}And it confuses me,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.70,1:21:55.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不知道以后到底会怎样  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- And I don't know what's gonna happen.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.86,1:21:57.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你将来会如何\N{\rENG}Let me tell you what's gonna happen, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.99,1:22:01.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,就跟平常一样\N{\rENG}the same thing that always happens...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.07,1:22:02.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么事都没有\N{\rENG}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.70,1:22:06.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,是 你知道吗 我没有一点自由时间\N{\rENG}Right, you know what? I have had absolutely zero time for myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.97,1:22:09.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还有一万封要回复的邮件\N{\rENG}I have ten thousand emails I have to answer
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.23,1:22:10.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没处理  - 等下\N{\rENG}- That I didn't answer.  - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.46,1:22:11.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你以为我没有吗  - 随便了\N{\rENG}- And you think I don't?  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.71,1:22:13.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,我整天都在做饭\N{\rENG}I spend all day making dinner,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.08,1:22:15.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,擦干你和你儿子在马桶坐垫上的尿\N{\rENG}and wiping both you and your son's pee off the toilet seat,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.58,1:22:17.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你却在跟同行小说家侃侃而谈\N{\rENG}while you talk to your fellow novelist:
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.51,1:22:19.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,哎呀哎呀 你真是个天才\N{\rENG}Blah, blah, blah. You are a genius!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.84,1:22:23.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,哎呀哎呀哎呀哎呀 不 你才是天才\N{\rENG}Oh, blah blah blah blah. No! You are a genius!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.82,1:22:26.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们跟亨利道别那一瞬间 你却说\N{\rENG}And the second we said goodbye to Henry you suggest that
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.27,1:22:27.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还是得放弃梦寐以求的工作\N{\rENG}maybe I should give up my dream job
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.85,1:22:29.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,就因为你情绪低落吗\N{\rENG}because you feel bad?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.16,1:22:30.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是 现在它就成了你梦寐以求的了\N{\rENG}Okay, now it's your dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.50,1:22:32.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天下午你都不确定你要接受这份工作\N{\rENG}This afternoon you weren't even sure you wanted it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.43,1:22:33.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在就成梦寐以求的了\N{\rENG}but now it's your dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.68,1:22:36.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说话从来就不算数是吧\N{\rENG}Do you ever listen to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.00,1:22:38.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 这就是我梦寐以求的\N{\rENG}Yes, it is my dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.11,1:22:40.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,我虽犹豫但不意味着我不想接受\N{\rENG}Just because I have doubts doesn't mean that I don't want it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.69,1:22:41.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,可是这跟你又有什么关系\N{\rENG}Alright, but why do you care?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.84,1:22:43.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每天都要在橄榄树下\N{\rENG}Every day you go on your two hours
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.33,1:22:46.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,花两个小时在冥想中散步\N{\rENG}contemplative walk under the olive trees.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.02,1:22:48.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,苏格拉底 你真该穿件袍子\N{\rENG}Socrates, oh you should get a robe.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.75,1:22:49.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,是一个小时\N{\rENG}It's an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.97,1:22:52.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 从你离开到回来\N{\rENG}No, by the time you leave and by the time you actually with us again,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.96,1:22:55.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是两个小时 换我就不行\N{\rENG}Two hours. You know, I could never do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.54,1:22:57.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,你实在太会享受了\N{\rENG}you are very good at taking care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.28,1:22:59.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就自己照顾自己 还要操心别的事情\N{\rENG}I take care of myself and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.33,1:23:02.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,去哪里都是你收拾自己的 我收拾别的\N{\rENG}We go somewhere you pack your bag and I pack everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.91,1:23:05.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你从来都不会让我收拾女儿的东西\N{\rENG}You would never let me pack the girls' shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.45,1:23:06.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,从来都不会\N{\rENG}Never!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.13,1:23:08.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为你会忘了拿鞋子 尽带些脏内裤\N{\rENG}'Cause there would be no shoes and plenty of dirty underwear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.68,1:23:10.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,是了是了 随便你说\N{\rENG}Yeah ok, alright, so says you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.48,1:23:11.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你有时间思考\N{\rENG}No, I am happy that you have time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.68,1:23:14.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,有关宇宙与生存的问题 我很开心\N{\rENG}to contemplate the universe and have existential problems...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.33,1:23:17.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我没有 我几乎没有时间思考\N{\rENG}Because I don't. I barely have time to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.05,1:23:18.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我上班 带孩子\N{\rENG}I work, I babysit,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.36,1:23:20.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 上班 带孩子  - 你消停会行吗\N{\rENG}- I work, I babysit.  - Could you hold on a second?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.34,1:23:22.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想上个厕所\N{\rENG}I just have to tune up the string section.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.47,1:23:24.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗\N{\rENG}You know what?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.14,1:23:26.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,在办公室我只有\N{\rENG}The only time I get to think now
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.67,1:23:28.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,拉屎的时间能思考\N{\rENG}is when I take a shit at the office.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.15,1:23:30.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,伴着屎味整理思绪\N{\rENG}I'm starting to associate the thoughts with the smell of shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.78,1:23:34.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,这句话不错\N{\rENG}That is a good line!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.05,1:23:35.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要把这话用在书里\N{\rENG}I'm going to use that in a book someday.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.61,1:23:36.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 你一定会的\N{\rENG}Yeah, I'm sure you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.64,1:23:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,这句话就是整本书最好的句子了\N{\rENG}And that will be the best line in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.87,1:23:43.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有 不准再把我或我说过做过的\N{\rENG}And by the way, you may never ever use me or anything I say or do
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.01,1:23:44.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,写进你那些书里了\N{\rENG}in one of your fucking books again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.59,1:23:46.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,女儿们的也不可以\N{\rENG}and that goes for the girls, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.60,1:23:47.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,行\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.57,1:23:49.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是你不该跟作家搞在一起的 对吧\N{\rENG}You shouldn't have hooked up with a writer, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.53,1:23:52.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会把你写进书里的\N{\rENG}You weren't in the last book or the one I'm writing now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.23,1:23:54.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我他妈想写什么就写什么\N{\rENG}See, I'm gonna write about whatever the fuck I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.37,1:23:57.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们的生活还是你的素材  - 不不不\N{\rENG}- As always, our life works for you.  - No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.55,1:24:00.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,别再那装受虐媳妇的丑样子\N{\rENG}Don't give me this put-upon housewife bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.58,1:24:02.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 现在已经不是五十年代了\N{\rENG}Ok? This is not the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.03,1:24:05.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,抱歉打断你受压迫血泪史的激情讲述\N{\rENG}I'm sorry to ruin your perfect little narrative of oppression.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.17,1:24:07.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实上我才是\N{\rENG}With the truth but I'm the one
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.35,1:24:09.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,那个每天在家操心琐碎的人\N{\rENG}who's at home every day dealing with the bullshit,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.77,1:24:11.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 因为你六点半才下班  - 是六点\N{\rENG}- Cause you are working till 6:30  - Six o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.93,1:24:14.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你送女儿去学校 我去接\N{\rENG}You take the girls to school and I pick them up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.16,1:24:16.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样很公平 是我们约定好的\N{\rENG}that's fair, that's our deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.11,1:24:20.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 天 我们可是住在法国巴黎  - 对\N{\rENG}- We live in Paris, France, for Christ's sakes!  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.09,1:24:23.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你每天都要提醒我这事  - 我一生\N{\rENG}- And you remind me of it every single day.  - I have orbited
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.15,1:24:25.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,都在围着你转 你知道的\N{\rENG}my entire life around you and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.90,1:24:29.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我很抱歉这个暑假 你的确是度假\N{\rENG}Ok? So I'm sorry if this summer's vacation, and it is a vacation,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.32,1:24:31.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我只看到你在海里玩耍\N{\rENG}because all I've seen you do is frolic in the sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.49,1:24:33.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有不停地吃希腊沙拉\N{\rENG}and shove Greek salad down your throat.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.23,1:24:36.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,但这些并不能说明你花了时间\N{\rENG}Ok? But it's not indicative of you spending your life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.03,1:24:37.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,做家务\N{\rENG}In some kind of domestic servitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.64,1:24:39.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢男人什么吗\N{\rENG}You know what I love about men?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.29,1:24:41.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们依旧相信有魔法\N{\rENG}They still believe in magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.28,1:24:43.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,小精灵们帮他们收拾臭袜子\N{\rENG}Little fairies around who pick up the socks,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.73,1:24:46.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,把碗洗干净\N{\rENG}little fairies unload the dishwasher,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.20,1:24:48.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,给孩子们涂防晒油\N{\rENG}little fairies sunscreen the kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.12,1:24:49.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,做好希腊沙拉后\N{\rENG}little fairies who make the fucking
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.93,1:24:51.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,让你吃得像头猪一样\N{\rENG}Greek salad that you eat like a pig.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.85,1:24:53.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,行了 听我说 好吗\N{\rENG}Okay, listen to me, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.52,1:24:55.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你把我们照顾得很好\N{\rENG}You are great at taking care of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.41,1:24:56.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,这没错\N{\rENG}You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.78,1:24:59.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 你念着孩子\N{\rENG}I mean... you take care of the kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.02,1:25:01.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,想着朋友 心系整个社会\N{\rENG}you take care of your friends, you take care of the world, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.98,1:25:04.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你成为一个母亲之前就已经这样了\N{\rENG}And you were like that before you were a mom,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.50,1:25:06.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在更是爱心泛滥\N{\rENG}and now its only magnified, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.45,1:25:07.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.68,1:25:09.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,这也是我这些年一直强调的\N{\rENG}and I've been telling you this for years,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.42,1:25:10.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你得对自己上点心了 好吗\N{\rENG}now you gotta do a little bit better job
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.99,1:25:13.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,关心下自己\N{\rENG}taking care of yourself, ok? You do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.28,1:25:15.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后不要再以关心我做借口了 好吗\N{\rENG}Okay, stop patronizing me, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.87,1:25:18.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我才是每天六点在家 不是六点半\N{\rENG}I am the one at home every day at six, not 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.81,1:25:19.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很值得信赖\N{\rENG}I am reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.56,1:25:22.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,你请过保姆吗\N{\rENG}Have you ever booked a baby sitter ever in your entire life?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.99,1:25:23.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.30,1:25:26.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,女儿们的医生叫什么名字\N{\rENG}what is the name of their pediatrician?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.17,1:25:27.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要突击测试我\N{\rENG}Stop quizzing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.17,1:25:28.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你不知道  - 好吗 你也太无聊了\N{\rENG}- You don't know.  - Alright? it's really fucking boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.50,1:25:31.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吧 行 知道吗 我每晚都在家\N{\rENG}Yeah, okay... You know what? I'm at home every night,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.41,1:25:33.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,做饭 给孩子们洗澡\N{\rENG}and I make dinner, I give bath,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.71,1:25:34.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,给她们读睡前故事\N{\rENG}and I read bedtime stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.90,1:25:35.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候你在\N{\rENG}Sometimes you there,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.69,1:25:38.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候你学校又有事\N{\rENG}sometimes you at a university event,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.14,1:25:40.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,或是巡回宣传\N{\rENG}or a publicity tour, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.35,1:25:43.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你灵感一来就一直在写作\N{\rENG}When you get inspired you keep on writing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.69,1:25:45.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候我也会有灵感的 你知道吗\N{\rENG}I get inspired too sometimes, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.63,1:25:48.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你也想写东西 很好 你写嘛\N{\rENG}You want to write? Good, write.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.30,1:25:50.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 但你记得我曾是吉他唱手\N{\rENG}No, but you remember I used to sing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.32,1:25:52.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,还写词作曲吧\N{\rENG}and play guitar and write songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.48,1:25:54.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还是很喜欢做这个\N{\rENG}I'd still like to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.10,1:25:55.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我做不到 没时间\N{\rENG}But I don't get to, there isn't time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.94,1:25:59.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 首先 写作并不是我的兴趣爱好\N{\rENG}Ok... well, first off: My writing isn't a hobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.75,1:26:02.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 其次 我希望你能挤出点时间\N{\rENG}Alright? Secondly, I wish you would find the time...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.63,1:26:04.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,不知道你怎么有时间\N{\rENG}you somehow manage to find the time to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.25,1:26:06.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,抱怨一天工作八小时\N{\rENG}complain about eight hours a day!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.01,1:26:10.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你唱歌的样子 好吗\N{\rENG}I mean... I love the way you sing, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.79,1:26:13.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我抛弃一切追随你\N{\rENG}I fucked up my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.24,1:26:15.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,就因为你唱歌的样子 好吗\N{\rENG}'cause the way you sing, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.36,1:26:17.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你在牢骚 抱怨 忧虑中\N{\rENG}If you took one eighth of the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.80,1:26:22.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,分出八分之一的精力\N{\rENG}that you spend on bitching, whining, and worrying,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.29,1:26:24.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,放在音乐创作上\N{\rENG}if you put that energy into playing scales,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.90,1:26:27.40,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}姜戈·恩哈特{\u0}：法国著名吉他手，爵士乐史上的伟大琴师\N{\rCHS}你会成为姜戈·恩哈特这种人物的\N{\rENG}I mean you would like be fucking Django Reinhardt.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.90,1:26:33.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.53,1:26:36.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你忘了拿鞋子\N{\rENG}You forgot your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.89,1:26:59.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为你赢了吗\N{\rENG}You think you're winning?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.19,1:27:01.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,很少有人能体会到\N{\rENG}Very few people realize what it's like
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.90,1:27:04.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,对事业热情洋溢的女人有了孩子的感受\N{\rENG}for an active or passionate woman to have a child.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.77,1:27:06.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,有些朋友说 看吧\N{\rENG}Some friends told me that you'll see,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.96,1:27:08.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,迟早你会想着把她们扔出窗子\N{\rENG}you'll wanna throw them out the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.56,1:27:11.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实上我一点也不想伤害她们\N{\rENG}Okay? But the truth is that I never wanted to hurt them once,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.06,1:27:14.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我想过很多次要为自己结束这种生活\N{\rENG}but I thought about ending it all for myself a hundred times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.50,1:27:18.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很彷徨 而你又因亨利抚养权这破事\N{\rENG}I was so confused and you were always away on a stupid book tour
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.03,1:27:19.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是参加售书巡回活动\N{\rENG}because of Henry's custody shit,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.81,1:27:21.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我也不想跟你徒增烦恼\N{\rENG}and I didn't want to be a burden.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.77,1:27:22.91,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}西尔维娅·普雷{\u0}：美国女诗人，于创作高峰时自杀\N{\rCHS}现在我明白为何西尔维娅·普雷\N{\rENG}Now I know why Sylvia Plath
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.91,1:27:24.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,把头放进烤面包器里\N{\rENG}put her head in a toaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.67,1:27:26.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,是烤箱\N{\rENG}It was an oven.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.10,1:27:28.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要给我咬文嚼字 你知道我的意思\N{\rENG}Don't play with words! You know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.01,1:27:30.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,烤面包器 烤箱 都一个意思\N{\rENG}Toaster, oven! Same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.37,1:27:33.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道有多少次我独自面对女儿们的哭泣吗\N{\rENG}You know how many times I was alone with the girls crying?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.26,1:27:34.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我完全不知道怎么办\N{\rENG}With no clue what to do? Do you know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.84,1:27:37.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道当一个母亲不知所措时她的负罪感吗\N{\rENG}the guilt a mother feels when she doesn't know what to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.25,1:27:40.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为只有你有这种感觉吗\N{\rENG}Do you think you have sole ownership of that feeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.78,1:27:43.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你根本不明白好吗\N{\rENG}I don't think you understand, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.59,1:27:46.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我内心对男人恐惧的是什么吗\N{\rENG}You know what my secret fear is with every man?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.78,1:27:50.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,是他们都想把我变成一个顺从的主妇\N{\rENG}Is that they all want to turn me into a submissive housewife.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.35,1:27:53.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 没人能那样做\N{\rENG}Ok... no one could ever do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.93,1:27:56.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 我保证\N{\rENG}Alright? I promise it would be easier
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.80,1:27:59.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,要让你顺从什么\N{\rENG}to fit your head into a toaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.07,1:28:01.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,还不如把你的头按进烤箱里更容易\N{\rENG}than to turn you into anything submissive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.12,1:28:04.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得我生育以后就没恢复过来\N{\rENG}I don't think I recovered since giving birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.30,1:28:06.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们出生时我完全不知道怎么办\N{\rENG}When they were born I had no idea of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.71,1:28:09.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…人们指望女人有天生的母性\N{\rENG}what to do, I.... People expect women
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.55,1:28:13.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,好像是突然冒出来的 就像母狒狒\N{\rENG}to have this instinct that kicks in. Like a female baboon.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.20,1:28:16.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我不知道该怎么做\N{\rENG}But I had no idea how to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.51,1:28:21.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很爱她们 但我做什么都是错的\N{\rENG}I love them so much and I was doing everything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.45,1:28:23.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还总不在家\N{\rENG}And you were away so often,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.62,1:28:26.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,打电话问我这一天过得怎么样\N{\rENG}and calling me and asking me how my day went.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.50,1:28:27.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我都不知道怎么和你说\N{\rENG}I couldn't even say it to you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.81,1:28:30.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得不知所措很丢人\N{\rENG}because I felt so ashamed to be so clueless.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.00,1:28:33.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我觉得你很棒  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Look, I think you did great.  - No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.48,1:28:36.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你很棒 起码假装得很棒\N{\rENG}No, you did, well you did a good job faking it then.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.69,1:28:38.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rENG}I just ..
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.05,1:28:40.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得哄她们睡觉唯一的办法就是\N{\rENG}I remember that the only way to get them to sleep
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.91,1:28:43.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,把笨重的双人婴儿车拖下楼\N{\rENG}was to drag that stupid double
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.22,1:28:46.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,在午夜几小时几小时的散步\N{\rENG}stroller down the stairs and walk them for hours and hours
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.70,1:28:49.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,走到皮加勒再返回来\N{\rENG}in the middle of the night, all the way to Pigalle and back.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.07,1:28:51.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,我有一次差点被抢劫\N{\rENG}I almost got mugged once, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.51,1:28:53.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,那家伙放过我的唯一原因\N{\rENG}the only reason why the guy didn't attack me
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.24,1:28:55.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我看上去太惨了\N{\rENG}was that I looked so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.06,1:28:57.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,过了三十五岁的唯一好处\N{\rENG}The only upside of being over 35
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.87,1:28:59.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是不用担心被强奸\N{\rENG}is that you don't get raped as much.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.38,1:29:05.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我看过这个说法 是真的  - 老天\N{\rENG}- I read it, it's true.  - Oh Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.14,1:29:09.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得我有一次\N{\rENG}Once I remember that I was watching
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.72,1:29:11.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,看到姐妹俩在跳蹦蹦床\N{\rENG}the twins on the trampoline, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.93,1:29:13.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们好漂亮\N{\rENG}and they looked so beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.12,1:29:17.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很开心因为她们开心\N{\rENG}and I was happy because they were happy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.17,1:29:18.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,其中一个用呼啦圈\N{\rENG}And one of them had this...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.04,1:29:23.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,跳绳用的那个\N{\rENG}Hulla-hoop that she was using as a jump rope, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.09,1:29:24.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,另一个也想\N{\rENG}But then the other wanted it,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.29,1:29:27.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她们就打起来了\N{\rENG}so they started fighting over it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.48,1:29:29.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,突然 被我看到了\N{\rENG}And all of a sudden, I saw it all, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.90,1:29:34.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有这些遗憾 嫉妒 自私\N{\rENG}All this, pity and jealousy and selfishness, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.20,1:29:41.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得我当时就在想 好吧这就是普遍人性\N{\rENG}And I remember thinking ... Ok, this is the natural human state
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.57,1:29:46.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是有点不满 永远不满足\N{\rENG}Always a little dissatisfied, perpetually discontented, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.71,1:29:47.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说\N{\rENG}I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.38,1:29:49.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,看看我们\N{\rENG}Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.70,1:29:54.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们在这 在这伊甸园\N{\rENG}Here we are, we are in... you know, The Garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.01,1:29:55.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我们还在争吵\N{\rENG}And we can not stop fighting.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.22,1:29:59.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不认为人性只有一面\N{\rENG}I do not think there is one natural human state.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.97,1:30:01.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,而是多面的\N{\rENG}The human state is multiple.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.24,1:30:02.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 如果你看到孩子们玩耍\N{\rENG}I mean, if that's what
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.19,1:30:04.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,想到的是这个\N{\rENG}you see when you're watching the girls play
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.88,1:30:06.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,说明你很沮丧\N{\rENG}that means you're depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.25,1:30:09.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.69,1:30:13.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 可能是吧  - 我看到她们打架时\N{\rENG}- Maybe I am.  - No. When I see them fight I see beautiful energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.70,1:30:15.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,看到的是生命中前行的无穷力量\N{\rENG}of going forward in life and not
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.42,1:30:18.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,不让任何人踩在她们头上 夺走她们想要的\N{\rENG}letting anyone step on them or take away what they want.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.46,1:30:21.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢她们打架 这让我看到了希望\N{\rENG}You know, I like it when they fight. It gives me hope for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.45,1:30:23.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是因为你把愤怒视作一种积极情绪\N{\rENG}Well that's cause you see anger as a positive emotion, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.96,1:30:27.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,最后只会伤害你自己 你的工作 孩子和我\N{\rENG}and you only end up hurting yourself, your work, the kids, me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.68,1:30:32.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,你从来不会生气吗\N{\rENG}And you never get angry?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.22,1:30:34.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,我生气时不会把它视作积极情绪\N{\rENG}When I do, I don't see it as a positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.30,1:30:38.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗\N{\rENG}You know something?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.40,1:30:43.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,你写的那些书 人们来找我\N{\rENG}The way you write in your books, people come up to me
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.86,1:30:47.65,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}亨利·米勒{\u0}：美国“垮掉派”作家\N{\rCHS}以为我和那些鲁莽的亨利·米勒式的男人滚床单\N{\rENG}and think that I make love to some wildcat Henry Miller type.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.93,1:30:54.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你滚床单的方式只有一种 每次都一样\N{\rENG}You like to have sex the exact same way. Every time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.81,1:30:58.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你说什么就是什么吧  - 亲亲 咪咪\N{\rENG}- When you got it you got it  - Kissy, kissy, titty, titty
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.52,1:30:59.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,下面\N{\rENG}Pussy...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.43,1:31:02.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是一个兴趣简单的男人\N{\rENG}I am a man of simple pleasures.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.28,1:31:05.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 非常简单\N{\rENG}Yeah, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.10,1:31:08.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我最近打算告诉你个事\N{\rENG}And I've been meaning to tell you that lately.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.83,1:31:10.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不是亨利·米勒\N{\rENG}You're no Henry Miller
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.26,1:31:12.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,在任何方面\N{\rENG}on any level.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.66,1:31:17.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 这房间让我浑身不自在\N{\rENG}You know what? This room gives me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.99,1:31:21.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我本来希望有一点古典的 真正的希腊风\N{\rENG}I was expecting something quaint, like the real Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.04,1:31:21.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,这地方真的很…\N{\rENG}This place is pretty real...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.61,1:31:23.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们来这到底干嘛\N{\rENG}What the hell are we doing here anyway?
